name: Cozy modern cottage near the city centre
description:
Lovely cottage close to the city centre. 10 mins to city centre by bus with closest bus stop 3min walk from house. LUAS (tram) is a 10min walk from the house. 40 min walk to city centre.
Free parking. Two bedrooms. One with double bed & second room with a daybed that can be pulled out to be a double bed.
Dogs live here but will not be present during stay, just to note in case anyone has strong allergies.
There is a lovely back garden with furniture & fire pit.
Real open fire in living room.

The space
The whole house will be available to you except for my own private bedroom. You will have access to the back garden as well & are welcome to use the kitchen.

Guest access
Parking to the side of the house without obstructing neighbours access. Back garden, front garden. Inside the house the only room that is not accessible is my own private bedroom.

Other things to note
The house does have dogs living
neighborhoodOverview: My house is very close to the city centre, it only takes 10mins by bus but is in a quiet residential area so you can get a good nights sleep after exploring the city . It is also about 20min walk to Kilmainham where there is a museum of modern art & the famous Kilmainham jail. The Luas which is a 10min walk from the house takes you into the city centre, Heuston Train Station, Connelly Station, The Red Cow among many other useful stops.

name: Self-contained ensuite bedroom with private access
description:
Self contained en-suite bedroom with private entrance & parking. Newly refurbished so first letting (November 2020). King size bed with TV & WiFi included. Cosy electric heating & large shower. Continental breakfast provided. No cooking facilities available, however fridge in room.
Located just off the Drimnagh Road beside main bus routes into the city. 10 mins walk to Our Lady's Hospital (Crumlin Children's Hospital). Maybe suit healthcare staff working night shifts. Very quiet location.

name: Cosy apartment in Chapelizod
description:
My place is very cosy and has very comfortable queen size bed. I also have a sofa bed in the living room, which is very comfortable for another two people two sleep on. Right outside the house is a bus stop which brings you to the town within 15 mins. It is 5 mins to Phoenix Park, Zoo and 15 minutes walk to the War Memorial Gardens. There are shops right around the corner so you can get whatever you might need. Across the road are two local pubs and a few restaurants where locals usually go.

The space
My apartment is a one bedroom apartment with separate bathroom and living space, which has a very comfortable sofa bed for other two people.
neighborhoodOverview: The apartment is 15 mins bus ride to town in charming Chapelizod. It is a quite area of Dublin, family friendly... You can easily get to parks, Guinness Factory and other attraction of Dublin.

name: Wonderful double room in Ireland
description: Light and colourful room in Dublin 12

name: Double bedroom in cosy Dublin house
description:
You will love our cosy double bedroom in our warm and welcoming home! All modern fittings and clean shared bathroom will make your stay very comfortable! Our kitchen is new and fitted with all appliances, with adjoining dining and living room for your enjoyment. We are in an excellent location 15/20mins from the heart of Dublin City. 5mins drive to M50. Kilmainham Goal and IMMA are within 10min stroll, the Phoenix Park, National Museum, Guinness Storehouse and Heuston Station are within 10mins by tram! Perfect for your city break!

Guest access
Free Parking
Wifi
Kitchen
neighborhoodOverview: Quaint suburb resting on the banks of the canal! Walking distance to historical sites and beautiful parklands! So close to the heart of the city and linked to surrounding attractions of Dublin by the m50!

name: Large period house, double ensuite, 15mins to city
description:
We are not taking guests until this Covid19 thing settles down. Hoping to host again towards the start of September

Our Master guest bedroom has a private ensuite with rain shower, timber floors, large wardrobe and a lovely double sleigh bed plus views of the front garden and streetscape. We believe our home is pretty unique property which we restored over the past 15 years to a very high standard and we enjoy hosting as a hobby.

The space
On arrival you can expect conversation, coffee a glass of wine.

Throughout your stay you are welcome to enjoy our Nespresso coffee or the selection of French tea's plus to kickstart your first morning with us we will provide a complementary continental breakfast.

Depending on circumstances we sometimes offer a second room which is a double room again ensuite (check with you about availability).

Guests have full access to the house including the kitchen, living room, gardens etc

name: Cosy flat nestled in the trees.
description:
Our home is situated on the edge of Chapelizod, one of the oldest villages in Dublin and just 7km from Dublin city centre.
The Phoenix Park and River Liffey are just two of our local amenities. Our large garden has plenty of space for parking but we also have a great bus service within 5 minutes walk. We are looking for longer term guests for 4 to 6 months. Rent is €1200 per month plus Airbnb fees.

name: 'Grace Gifford' cottage, Kilmainham
description:
One of four apartments in "Tigh Tirconaill", that we have named after Irish nationalist leaders to reflect our location in the historic Kilmainham/Inchicore area. Our Grace Gifford cottage comfortably sleeps 4 with a double bed in the bedroom and a double sofa bed in the living room.

The space
One of three apartments in "Tigh Tirconaill", The "Grace Gifford" cottage is cozy, warm and quiet. The bedroom has a double bed with the bathroom ensuite. The living room has comfortable leather furniture with a pull out sofa bed for extra sleeping accommodation.

There is a nice dining area overlooking the patio and a compact kitchen. The bedroom has one double bed and also a fold up single bed which is suitable for a child. Nice spacious bathroom with walk in power shower. Situated to the rear of the property overlooking the patio, you will be cosy and comfortable staying in the "Grace Gifford" cottage.

Location:

Close to Kilmainham Ga
neighborhoodOverview:
Conveniently situated close to 'The Dubline' Dublin Discovery Trail, featuring Kilmainham Gaol and Courthouse and The Royal Hospital Kilmainham, Ireland's oldest public building dating back to 1684. We are just a short walk to the War Memorial Gardens. Our apartments have been restored with great care and attention to detail, retaining the original Victorian features providing classic, comfortable and select accommodation in Dublin. Our apartments are upmarket with attention to detail and our guest comfort our priority. Easy access to all the top restaurants, pubs, museums and attractions that Dublin has to offer. For those who prefer a quicker route than the Dubline trail, the bus stop is almost outside the door with route 13 serving Guinness Storehouse, Christchurch Cathedral, Dublin Castle, Temple Bar, Trinity College and O'Connell St.
A 5 minute walk to the Luas red line,travelling via The Museum at Collins Barracks, The Jameson Distillery, Jervis St., Dublin Convention Centre

name: 1 bedroom Apt. with full facilities. Close to City
description: My place is close to parks. You’ll love my place because of Quiet area but still just 5k from Dublin city., the comfy bed, the neighbourhood, the kitchen, the cosiness. My place is good for solo adventurers, business travellers, I share my home with a cat.

name: Double bedroom next to Phoenix park
description: Comfortable and cosy double bedroom, situated in a quite 3 bedroom house next to Phoenix park. One couple is living in the house. Bus station is 50 m from the house, 10 min drive to city center (3 lines operates). It is close to Kilmainham Jail, Museum of Modern art, Memorial Gardens and Phoenix park.

name: Cosy family home in Walkinstown
description:
Beautiful family home within walking distance of shops, playground, library, cafés and local pubs with food and entertainment. On direct bus and tram routes to the city centre, close to the M50 and 20 minutes by car to Dublin Airport.

Guest access
The complete house is available to enjoy but the attic is not available for air bnb guests.

Other things to note
There are 3 beds in the bunk bed, 2 are suitable for adults but the top bunk would be best suited for 12year olds and younger. There is a baby cot and a double bed also.

name: Lumy
description: Nice, simple bedroom located in a quiet area. 25 min away from the city centre.

name: Comfy room in the heart of the city
description:
Cosy, private single room in a comfortable top floor apartment located in the heart of the city. A stones' throw from Trinity College, it is in walking distance of most major attractions such as Temple Bar, Dublin Castle, Steven's Green and many others. Close by there is a Tesco supermarket and other small shops.

You will be able to use the kitchen which is fully equipped. I live with two friendly PhD students studying in Trinity, who are good company.

The space
The place is a top floor apartment with good views of the city and a balcony. Guests are provided with freshly cleaned bedding and towels and can use a hair dryer in the room.

name: Contemporary 3 Bedroom Townhouse Dublin Central
description:
This is a great opportunity to stay in a unique development "Rafters Court" well-designed properties. This well proportioned end of terrace townhouse is one of five built and finished to a very high standard and are ideally located for a family getaway or a couple’s retreat close to Dublin city and the surrounding countryside for a great Dublin Vacation.

The space
The house has a spacious open plan living and dining area with amtico flooring throughout. A fully equipped kitchen with crockery & cutlery and pots & pans, a microwave oven and a kettle, toaster and everything you will need to make your stay feel like a "home from home". Off the main entrance hall is the guest bathroom. There are three bright and spacious double bedrooms, all with built in wardrobes and one bedroom with it's own private ensuite. Located next to the bedrooms on the first floor there is also a large family bathroom. The house has off street parking for one car and a sunny south-facing r
neighborhoodOverview: This Townhouse has an excellent location. It is situated on the corner of the Crumlin road in a quality mature residential area with a short walk to a good selection of Shops, Bars and Restaurants and the many amenities this area has to offer.

name: Comfortable family home close to Dublin centre.
description: This is a comfortable family home with three bedrooms and comfortable living and dining rooms.   The kitchen is fully equipped and the distance from the city centre is four kilometres.   There are seven bus services available within five minutes walk of the house.

name: Near City Centre (bus and nite bus)
description:
20 minutes by bus to City Centre and there are lots of buses!
ONE MONTH MINIMUN STAY at €650 each month.
Double bed in large room (single occupancy only).
Our home is more suited to Female visitors at this time.

The space
Local shops 2 mins walk include SPAR, Pharmacy, Butcher, Hair salon, Convenience Store, Chinese take away etc. Local pubs serving lunch and evening meals only 10mins stroll.
Own key to come and go as please.

As our guests, we want you to feel at home, even if only for a short stay. Enjoy kitchen facilities, cable tv, living room. Washing machine and dryer available (small charge).

We come and go on different daily schedules. We are welcoming but don't stand on formalities. Make yourself at home...that means, get your own cuppa tea and be comfortable. There is a family dog, he is mostly outside during the day but likes to say hello when you come home.

Access to City Centre! Locally, the sh

name: Contemporary City Centre Cottage
description:
Our home is a newly renovated terraced cottage, in the heart of Dublin City. An ideal location for exploring the city highlights.

The space
Our home is located in a quiet street & provides all the all the comforts of a home away from home.

Guest access
The entire place (ground floor) is available to our guests, complete with lounge, dining area, kitchen, wet room, double bedroom, yard area. An additional room, on the ground floor complete with blow up mattress can be arranged on request.
neighborhoodOverview: The house is located in an up & coming neighborhood close to Portobello. There are plenty of restaurants & cafe's to suit all budgets in the locality, as well as a variety of grocery stores.

name: 3 Bed Ensuited Space Free Parking & City Tram Line
description:
1. Location on tram line which takes 15 min to City Centre,Temple Bar and all other major attractions including Trinity College, Guinness store house and Kilmainham Jail. Trams are regular between 2 & 5 min. This is a great link to the city & its attractions. Private Free Car Parking.
2. Stunning Home with All 3 bedrooms fully ensuited & each room has king size beds as well as being extremely quiet & spacous. Ideal for large groups, Families & Business users.
3. Personal check in organised.

The space
1. This is a great apartment suited for hosting up to 6 guests in a very quiet apartment complex.
2. Apartment is in safe secure compound with secure parking for your car.
3. Apartment is 2 min walk from shops; 2 local bars / restaurants and also only a 3 min short walk from the tram line which shall bring you to the city centre within 15 mins. Please see Guidebook at the bottom of this page.
4. All three Bedrooms are large with Kingsize
neighborhoodOverview:
1. The apartment is on the tram line which brings you all the way to the City centre and the Temple Bar area. The tram also stops close to the Guinness store house and a short walk from Trinity College and the main shopping district around Grafton Street.
2. We are very close to 3 local Bars and Supermarkets. Aldi, Supervalu, Lidl and Centra are less than 10 minute walk away.
3. Costa cafe and two local restaurants are also five minute walk away.

name: Best Dublin Central View Apartment
description:
Hi There,

Mona here.

My apartment is literally a stones throw across from St Patrick's Cathedral and Marsh's Library right around the corner.

You could say I live in a golden mile of places to see and things to do. Food, fashion, pubs, cafe's of all sorts and sizes are all on my doorstep.

I love it and I hope you will too .......




I love

name: Traveler's home;) 15min walk to city centre
description:
Welcome to our house! Our place is not super fancy place but me and my husband love meeting people, having guests.
This room is for single traveler (double bed , share the bathroom). The room is on the ground floor next to the bath room.
Our living room was changed decoration and and your room changed wall colour to light blue.
My place is close to Aircoach bus stop, shop, local pubs. You’ll love my place because of the neighbourhood.

Guest access
Your guest room, bathroom, living & kitchen room

Other things to note
This is a family home. We have a boy being 2 years in April and are expecting another baby. We also have a Japanese aupair living in attic. We both have jobs but I also work at home from Tuesday to Thursday. If you stay here, I'll be out to do job. But the house isn't empty all the time.
Our living room is upstairs so you can relax at night time. Although it's beside the bathroom and we share that, it's a bit
neighborhoodOverview: There is a convinience store 2 mins walking distance. There are local pubs where you can have one of the best Guinness and popular cafes and restaurants. You can even walk to the city centre easily. Big supermarket is also within 10min.

name: Grand Canal Place
description: Nice private room with its own bathroom in a 2 bedroom flat in Grand Canal. Very comfortable place at walking distance (15 min) from city centre and very handy to/from airport (20' by bus). Only a 2 min walk to bars, restaurants, theatre and cafes.

name: Comfy double bedroom in spacious flat city center
description:
This nice and spacious flat is only two minutes walking from Merrion Square and 10 minutes from Trinity College.
Great location in city center.

name: Double bedroom in great Dublin city location!
description:
Bright double bedroom with balcony access. The property is ideally located in the picturesque village of Chapelizod. We are a short walk to the beautiful Phoenix Park, Europe's largest public park, if you fancy an active day out. Close to public transport; the city centre is only 10 minutes by bus where you can explore Dublin city and its famous attractions. Chapelizod is a 15 minute drive from Dublin Airport and less than 5 minute drive to Heuston train station.

The space
You will love your stay here as Chapelizod is a lovely, relaxing area. Our apartment is nice and cosy and we are friendly, helpful and knowledgeable on the local area if you have any queries or need any recommendations for exploring the city centre.

Guest access
Guests have access to the kitchen & living room area.

Other things to note
We really hope you enjoy your stay with us. We have some maps of the local area and happy to give any recommendatio
neighborhoodOverview: Chapelizod is a lovely, quiet, relaxed area with a shop, pharmacy, church and two local pubs, all less than 5 minute walk away. There are regular buses into the city centre and the bus stop is 2 minute walk from the apartment.

name: 2 bedrooms terraced house/ Petite maison de ville
description:
2 bedrooms terraced house. Near all amenities and Phoenix Park. 20 min bus ride to city centre.
Petite maison de ville. Près de magasins, d'arrêts de bus et de Phoenix Park (15/20 minutes à pied). Petit jardin verdoyant (pour les fumeurs).
Possibilité de rajouter un matelas gonflable deux places (fournis) dans la chambre 1 personne.
Quartier calme, voisins agréables et discrets et un parc avec ère de jeux à 100m de la maison (idéal pour de jeunes enfants).

name: Charming Dublin Home - Real Irish Experience
description:
(Please Inquire as to the room(s) you wish to book in advance of booking. They may be subject to availability)

Our home offers an authentic taste of the delight that Dublin has to offer. It is a perfect place to relax after a day exploring our emerald Ireland's many attractions, or simply just to kick back and unwind

The house is shared with permanent tenants so airbnb guests must be respectful of the others sharing

The space
The house is calm, warm and homely.

Living space:
A tranquil space to relax on your own or with your group. You are welcome to enjoy the space in silence, in conversation, with a book, watching a show, with your own choice of music, or however you may feel appropriate.

Kitchen:
The kitchen is very well equipped as Ronan is a passionate cook. There is ample storage space for food in fridges or in cupboards. Pots, pans, cutlery and other cooking equipment are free to use as is our gas ove
neighborhoodOverview:
Our house is located on a very quiet, safe and peaceful lane way in an urban neighbourhood, close to shops, pubs and restaurants.

However public transport, or a short taxi ride would bring you to areas of greater energy, excitement (eg. nightlife) should you be in the market for it :)

name: The Fleet, Deluxe Small Double Room
description:
The space
We have rooms suitable for all types of travelers, whether for business, pleasure, romantic holidays, and more. Each of our rooms are individually decorated for a unique look and feel. You’ll have a warm, welcoming feeling with the autumn tones of the soft furnishings and rich fabrics. Beds are topped with crisp linen and en suite bathrooms have complimentary amenities.

The Fleet Street Hotel is located in the centre of Dublin, bordering Temple Bar. We are minutes away from the popular Grafton Street or O’Connell St. for shopping, dining, and entertainment. You can also visit the nearby Trinity College or The Guinness storehouse.

Each room includes:
Free WiFi
Flat screen satellite TV
Tea and coffee maker

name: Double Bedroom with Shared Bathroom (F)
description: Stunning Duplex apartment situated superbly in Dublin's Docklands. Minutes from Grand Canal Dock DART and other amenities such as quayside bars, restaurants, cafes and shops.

name: Cliffs of Moher Country House
description:
Our seaside property is set it the heart of the countryside in a tranquil country setting with the iconic cliffs of moher just a mile up the road. If you love nature, hiking and the ocean, then this is the place for you. Covid update ** Extra measures in place to make certain your room & bathroom are sanitized and safe. This is the ideal place to come for your post lockdown getaway. The Burren, The cliffs and much more all on your doorstep.

The space
The only sounds you will hear are the ocean, the gulls, the cows and the odd tractor passing by. We are truly on the Wild Atlantic way and the weather can be volatile being so close to the Cliffs and the ocean. We are a mile from the Cliffs of Moher and 2 miles from the very pretty Liscannor Village. When you walk out the front door here you are only metres from the atlantic ocean. The hikes around here are second to none.

Guest access
In addition to the shared kitchen, you have access to
neighborhoodOverview: The Cliffs of Moher, The Burren national park and the Aran islands are at our doorstep, so is Doolin. This location is ideal for adventurers. There is a lovely patisserie and a cracking pub in the village of Liscannor.  Close by in the village of Lahinch you will find many restaurants, bars and great surfing.

name: Cozy & fancy double room in a great location
description: Cozy apartment in a great location (5 minutes from Merrion Square Park and 10 minutes from Trinity College/City Centre). Apartment surrounded by Art Galleries, Museums, Coffee Shops and lovely restaurants. Comfortable double room, Wi-Fi, heating, blankets, towels and nice breakfast.

name: Friendly, cosy and convenient room
Lahinch View 2
description: Lahinch View is situated in a prime location in the greenvale of Kilshanny, overlooking Lahinch, a stone's throw from Ennistymon and in close proximity to Lisdoonvarna and Doolin.  The Burren, Cliffs of Moher, Aillwee Cave, Aran Islands and many other tourist attractions are all within short driving distance. It is located off the main Lisdoonvarna Road - take the L1056 exit.  Homemade fresh bread and scones will be baked to accompany your continental breakfast.

name: Boutique Townhouse in the Heart of Dublin
description: Sink into facing couches for a cosy conversation next to a fireplace carved into an exposed stone wall. Sense the history occupying every corner of this former cobbler's workshop which has been carefully transformed by a designer's sensitive touch.
neighborhoodOverview: The townhouse is located in Dublin 2, a five-minute walk from Grafton Street. St Stephens Green Park is one minute away. It's within comfortable walking distance of Temple Bar, Trinity College, the National Concert Hall, and National Art Gallery.

name: 5min walk to Grafton St, Quiet Double Bed Room
description:
Comfy double bed room in a lovely, comfortable and clean apartment. It is located in a very central area, next to St Stephens Green, 5min walking to Grafton street and just 8 min walk to Temple bar! Light breakfast (coffee, tea ...) , towels, basic elements and touristic info is included. Welcome home ! We accept last minute bookings!

The space
Secure Residential building, very quiet building just minutes away from all attractions

Guest access
You will have access to the balcony, kitchen, living room, and bathroom (shared with my wife and I). Wifi of course!
neighborhoodOverview: Quiet neighborhood, close the night life and all main attractions

name: Apache Hostel Temple Bar
The Ramblers Rest B&B - 2.1km From Cliffs Of Moher
description:
The Ramblers Rest B&B is located less than 2 km from the Cliffs of Moher and a 10-minute drive from Doolin. Doolin has lots of lovely pubs and restaurants, This charming rural property offers great views of the Atlantic Ocean, the Aran Islands, and Galway Bay. Each of the rooms at the family-run B&B has traditional décor. All rooms have a private bathroom and heating. Free WiFi is available. The surrounding area is ideal for coastal walks. Lahinch Golf Club is only a 15-minute drive.

The space
Our Bed & Breakfast is very unique and different conpared to other B&Bs around Ireland. We have fantastic views, comfy bed and a hearty Full Irish Breakfast. What more could you ask for ? 😊

Guest access
Guests have access to the lounge area where they can kick back and relax. They also have access to the garden area where they sit down and look at are magnificent views.
neighborhoodOverview: Doolin is a fantastic place to live. Where we are situated, we have fantastic views of the sea. Everyone is also very friendly and nice.

name: Triple Room
description: My place is close to Bord Gáis Energy Theatre trinity College & Aviva Stadium .

name: Lahinch Railway Cottage, Perfect Location!
description: Cosy one bed room appartment in the heart of Lahinch

name: City Penthouse, Own Balcony, Shower
description:
Location, location, location, - City and beach - and minutes to all the International companies located in our area, 15 mins straight walk into the city centre and 5 mins to the beautiful beach. Airport 15 mins on bus. Buses, trains, trams and taxis all minutes away or Walk to city centre like the locals. Check-out our Reviews.

The space
Bright, light filled Xlarge Penthouse Bedroom with yr own super-clean private bathroom.

Your own small private balcony overlooking a quiet courtyard with views.

Peace & quiet.

Free & fast wifi in room.

A good size work-desk & LED lamp, adjustable chair & foot rest for extensive desk work.

Own fridge in room and tea/coffee and kettle with fresh water.

European Duvet & four pillows on a Super king size bed.

Fresh towels & toiletries ( conditioner, shampoo, shaving cream, ) all provided.

Hairdryer provided.

Free on Street
neighborhoodOverview: The neighbourhood is charming and close to all amenities, pubs, live music, beach walks and promenades.  Quiet, very very safe and convenient. Most locals walk into the city centre from here although there are also plenty of buses.   Stroll down to the beach 5 mins away. Our guests enjoy privacy.

name: Temple Bar's Bridge View
description:
Bright apartment with the best view in town of Dublin's most iconic Ha'penny bridge

Other things to note
For stays longer than 2 weeks:
If electricity bills amount to more than 100 euro/ 2 weeks we will ask the guest to pay the surplus.

name: Amazing Ensuite Double Bedroom
description: Double bedroom with a king size bed. Private bathroom. The bedroom has amazing views to the Grand Canal in a big terrace. New design apartment with a big living room, a modern kitchen and a parking space also available in case you need it. Wi-Fi provided.

name: Perfect Holiday Location, Restaurants
description:
Perfectly located in quiet quaint fishing village of Liscannor. A modern warm and cosy 2 bedroom (both ensuite) duplex apartment. First floor with steps up to own entrance, across road from popular seafood restaurants and friendly traditional pubs. 2 mins walk to pier and picnic area. 5 mins drive to Lahinch, famous for golf and surfing, 7 mins to Cliffs of Moher. Ideal for touring Clare inc The Burren, Doolin & Lisdoonvarna.

The space
Aside from the proximity of the many tourist attractions, the luxury of just crossing the road at the end of a busy day to enjoy a choice of 3 popular traditional pubs with great food, friendly atmosphere and music most nights, really add to the holiday experience, while at the same time being in a very quiet and peaceful area.

One of the major attractions in the area is the Cliffs of Moher Coastal Walk commencing at Liscannor, as you walk you will have great views of Liscannor Bay, the cliffs and Lahinch. You ca

name: Georgian Dublin meets Silicone Docks. Private room
description:
Bright en suite bedroom in a beautifully renovated 200 year old artisan cottage in the very centre of Georgian Dublin.
Next door to Merrion Square, Dublin Grand Canal, The National Gallery Art, The Natural History museum and Ireland Government buildings.
Close to first rate cafes, restaurants, galleries, weekend food markets, bars and cultural walks.

10 mins to Grafton Street and Trinity College.
Around the corner from Google, National Conference Centre, Aviva Stadium and the Docklands.

The space
Built in 1815, this terrace cottage has been renovated beautifully in the heart of Georgian Dublin.

Guest access
Guests will have access to a private coffee machine, High speed Wifi and access to the Kitchen for cooking.
Car parking is pay and display along the street (free on Saturday & Sundays)
neighborhoodOverview:
You are in the heart of Dublin 2 (Dublin City centre)
just 100m away from the stunning Merrion Square - The where food and Art fairs are held each week.
A leisurely walk from your front door will bring you to the birth place of Oscar Wilde, The National Gallery of Ireland, The Natural History Museum and Irelands Government Buildings.
Wine and Dine in michelin star restaurants and lunch, brunch and snack in the numerous hip cafes surrounding the house.
You will be based in the centre of Ireland very own silicone valley with all tech headquarters like Facebook and Google within walking distance, this gives the area a great buzz and sense of excitement.
Being at the heart of Dublin also means that shopping is never more than a 10min walk, whether you are looking for high end designer goods, high street or vintage we will be able to direct you to the best spots Dublin has to offer.

name: HANOVER DOCK-CORPORATE HUB TO HSBC,GOOGLE&FACEBOOK
description:
***Location Location Location***Waterfront living*** Situated in this highly sought after location in the heart of Grand Canal Dock, one of Dublins most fashionable & vibrant city districts. The city centre, Ballsbridge, the IFSC and Sandymount are all within walking distance while the DART and LUAS are also within a short stroll. Grand Canal Dock is home to major employers including HSBC, Google and Facebook, with many major blue-chip accountancy firms and law firms also at home in the area.

The space
This vibrant Dublin 2 pocket has a ton of amenities including gyms, cafes, restaurants, bars, sports clubs and more. It is also home to the Marker Hotel and the famous Grand Canal Theatre. Bank of Ireland, KBC and AIB are amongst the major banks located in the immediate area. Grand Canal is home to major international employers such as Air Bnb, Facebook, Google and other marketing and technology companies.
Stylish, modern, luxurious 2 bedroom apartment in a ce
neighborhoodOverview: The area is well serviced with transport: Dublin Bikes, the Dart Station (Grand Canal Dock), the Luas and Dublin Bus however the location is second to none and Dublin City Centre, Ballsbridge, Sandymount and the IFSC are all within walking distance. Grand Canal is approximately 1.8 km from Trinity College and other well-known colleges are in nearby and accessible areas.

name: 2-BR, 2 BTH secure & peaceful Dublin 4
description:
Welcome to my home in Dublins tech hub!

This 2 bedroom apartment is situated in a secure complex in one of Dublins best neighbourhoods.

The complex has a rooftop terrace with benches which overlooks the fantastic views of Dublin City.

Perfect for business travellers as it is on the doorstep of the numerous tech offices close-by. However, tourists will also love the ability to walk to all of the sights Dublin has to offer or to hop on the DART (Grand Canal Station is on its doorstep)

The space
Bedroom1: double bed, en suite bathroom
Bedroom2: double bed
Kitchen: fully equipped with everything that you need: oven, hob, fridge/ freezer, coffee french press.
Bathroom: shower
Bathroom2: ensuite with bathtub
Balcony: the living room has an attached small balcony which allows light to pour in and fill up the room.
Roof terrace: beautiful views of the city with benches to sit back and relax
neighborhoodOverview:
The immediate area has seen a huge influx of the likes of Google, Facebook and the improved national football stadium (the Aviva) moving in just down the road.

Close to the apartment you’ll also find the RDS Arena. On Pembroke Road, Leeson Street or Morehampton Road, you will find plenty of eateries, coffee shops, groceries shops, bars and restaurants a short walk from the apartment.

Please take a look at the guidebook on my listing for recommended places to eat and drink in the area!

name: Three Double Ensuite Rooms
description:
Our two spacious double ensuite rooms, and cosey double room with separate bathroom are located just a short 5 minute stroll from the center of the village - overlooking the Cliffs of Moher.
Guests have access to their own kitchenette where tea/coffee making facilities can be found, and a complimentary continental breakfast is provided.

The space
The house is located just a short five minute stroll from the center of Doolin, where you’ll find famous traditional Irish pubs, with plenty of craic, ceoil and good food.
Just ~500m from one of Doolin’s many bus stops with services from Dublin, Galway and Limerick.
Both Bus Eireann and Paddywagon provide regular shuttle buses to and from Cliffs of Moher during the summer months.

Your bedroom is a stylish minimalist space with crisp li

The stunning views and sunsets over the Aran Islands ensure the ideal setting for relaxation.

The space

The accommodation consists of a downstairs bright open plan living area with Smart HD TV, books, DVDs, a comfy couch and a fully equipped kitchen (fridge freezer, washing machine, microwave, 4 ring gas cooker and oven, kettle and toaster). The kitchen is also stocked with tea, coffee and utensils. We also provide a few breakfast items such as milk, juice, jams, fresh fr
neighborhoodOverview: Doolin is a truly unique village in the west of Ireland, where visitors are captivated by the long-established traditional music scene, inviting pubs, storytelling, lively conversation and excellent food and drink. A trip to the charming Aran Islands is accessible by ferry from Doolin Pier. Doolin Cave is home to the longest free-standing stalactite in Europe. An 18-hole Pitch and Putt course with coastal views is located between Fisher Street and Doolin Pier. The Cliffs of Moher are also accessible by the coastal clifftop walking path which runs from Doolin to Liscannor. We are also a short drive from The Burren national geo park, Lahinch beach, Aillwee Cave and Fanore beach. There is a food store and petrol station with an ATM 2.2km/4minutes drive away.

neighborhoodOverview:
My favourite spots:
•O'Donoghues - Built in 1789 as a grocery store and serving pints since 1934. A traditional Irish pub with live music. The Dubliners, Christy Moore and Phil Lynott have spent many a memorable night entertaining Dublin's music lovers in this bar.
•Slattery’s (Capel St.) - Anthony Bourdain recommends the full Irish breakfast here. One of the few remaining ‘Early Houses’ which means you can legally enjoy a nice frosty Guinness from as early as 7:30am to accompany your brekkie.
•The Long Hall - Licensed since 1766, The Long Hall is one of Dublin’s oldest, most beautiful and best loved pubs, abundant in traditional charm and exuding genuine Victorian originality, and the interior dates from 1881. Irish rock legend Phil Lynott recorded here the video for his hit-song ‘Old Town’ in 1982. Rihanna and Bruce Springsteen are known to enjoy pints here when on tour.

**** PLEASE CROSS CHECK THE AVAILABILITY OF THE APARTMENT BEFORE SENDING THE BOOKING REQUESTS*****

Its a perfect location for business travellers located in Grand Canal Dock with easy access to the City Centre.

The space
Positioned close to all major corporate offices in the Grand Canal Dock and is only a short walk to the IFSC, the new Convention Centre, the 3 Arena concert venue and the Grand Canal Theatre. This centrally located apartment boasts a great selection of fashionable restaurants, bars and shops all within walking distance.

It has direct access to the north side of the city via the Samuel Beckett bridge. It is well serviced by rail, bus, air link [to the airport] and water taxis. This is an ideal corporate base. Underground parking (at an extra cost), 24 hour CCTV coverage and aims to offer residents maximum convenience and comfort.

neighborhoodOverview: Set less than 1 km from The Convention Centre Dublin, it is situated in Dublin City Centre of Dublin. The EPIC The Irish Emigration Museum is within a 14-minute walk of the apartment.

name: *New* Temple Bar Modern Retreat in the Old City
description:
Newly refurbished apartment in the quietest spot of Temple Bar, located in Dublin city centre: Arts, music, shops, restaurants and bars are right at your doorstep. Direct bus from/to airport just 1-minute walking distance. You will be staying in a quiet yet vibrant lane, within a few minutes walk to the best attractions of the old city. The perfect place for couples, small families or business travellers, where up to 4 people can sleep comfortably.

The space
This bright and modern apartment has everything you need for an enjoyable stay. Newly refurbished open-plan with kitchen, living area, and dining area integrated, it has the perfect space to relax in and appreciate you travelling companion. The kitchen area is fully-equipped with all appliances and cutlery you will need for a short or long stay. There is one bedroom with double bed, and a large sofa-bed in the living area. Fresh soft linen and towels are provided. The apartment comfortably accommodates 4 peop
neighborhoodOverview: Staying in my apartment you will be in a quiet yet vibrant street of Temple Bar, within a short walking distance to Dublin’s main attractions: a 5-minute walk to Dublin Castle, Christchurch Cathedral, Dublinia, City Hall, Olympia Theatre and The Smock Alley Theatre. It is also only a 15-minute walk to Dublin’s best shops on Grafton Street, Trinity College and the Book of Kells, the unique St. Stephen’s Green Park, the City Center or to Saint Patrick’s Cathedral. In less than 8 minutes, you can get the Luas tram on Jervis Street and easily reach out to IFSC, 3 Arena, or Smithfield Square and Jameson Distillery.

name: Cloudbreak - Seafront Townhouse on Lahinch Prom
description:
Unobstructed sea/beach view. Property is located on the promenade along Lahinch beach. Ideally located for both the beach and main street of Lahinch. There is a balcony on the first floor and the main living area is also located on this floor. The single bedroom is on the ground floor, while the double and twin en-suite rooms are located on the top floor. There is private parking for one car located in the attached yard.

The space
There is a large main living area which has great views of the bay.

Guest access
You will be renting and have access to the entire house.
neighborhoodOverview: There are a large number of places to eat just a short walk from the house. The beach is the main attraction in Lahinch, weather it is for walking, swimming, surfing or building sand castles. There are two 18 hole golf courses in the town also, which hosted the Irish Open in 2019.

name: Apartment in D02 very close to Trinity College
description: Very central position, comfortable place

name: Penthouse D4 apartment
description:
Spacious 3 bed duplex apartment located 2 km from Grafton Street. Walking distance to the dart. 10/15 mins to Sandymount village. 1.7km to the convention centre (20 mins walk). Close to google/Aviva. 0.4 km to the Air B and B office (9 mins).

3 bedrooms available. 1 double with ensuite and downstairs there is 1 double and 1 single bed. 5 guests max
neighborhoodOverview: The duplex apt is located a 30 min walk from Grafton Street (2km). Close to the lovely village of Sandymount. It is also close to the IFSC and approx 1.7km to the convention centre.

name: Private Double/Family room with en-suite
description:
Situated in West Clare on the Wild Atlantic Way. 5 minutes from Miltown Malbay (host to the famous Willie Clancy Week) Situated near Lahinch and right across the bay from the Cliffs of Moher... quiet and peaceful area surrounded by beautiful countryside. Comfortable, king size bed, and ensuite bathroom, + 2 single beds.
Ideal place to rest and chill out. You can hear the ocean and song of the birds from the comfort of the bedroom.

The space
We are surrounded by nature and the ocean can be seen across the meadows. As long as you don't mind the sound of rain against the roof on occasion you will certainly get a good nights sleep.

Guest access
Tea and coffee
Hot water
Towels
internet
neighborhoodOverview:
We are situated between Miltown Malbay and Lahinch. Two popular destinations of the Wild Atlantic Way. Also surrounded by beautiful beaches and the rugged Clare coastline.
The area is rich in music and tradition. During the day there is a lot of walks in the area and at night the bars and restaurants offer good food and lots of live music.

name: Chic, modern and quiet space in heart of Dublin
description:
Chic, modern and quiet space in the heart of Dublin City centre.

Large double bedroom with private bathroom in the heart of Grand Canal Dock (Silicon Docks).

House has been beautifully renovated in 2018.

There are a number of quality restaurant and bar options in the immediate vicinity, with the house around the corner from the Bord Gais Theatre. Major sporting and concert venues within walking distance.

The space
House features:

- Newly installed, fully-equipped kitchen
- Newly renovated double bedroom
- New bed, mattress, bedding and spacious wardrobes
- Ultra high-speed internet
- TV in bedroom with full TV package (including Sky Sports, Sky Movies, Sky Entertainment)
- Spacious private courtyard
- Sole use of private bathroom
- Towels provided
neighborhoodOverview:
- In the centre of Dublin’s trendy Grand Canal Dock.
- 5 min walk to the Grand Canal.
- 10 min walk to Grafton Street area.
- 10 min walk to O’Connell Street area (the Spire!).
- 15 min walk to Aviva Sports Stadium.
- 15 min walk to the 3 Arena for concerts.
- Directly opposite the Bord Gais Energy Theatre.
- 5 min walk to DART train stations for day trips out of Dublin.
- 20 min journey to Dublin Airport (serviced by multiple bus routes).

- Surrounded by quality restaurants/ brunch spots and lively bars!

name: Townhouse
description: The flat is situated in a quiet area, within easy walking distance are St. Stephens Green, Grafton Street, Aviva Stadium, Bord Gais Theatre, The Olympia Theatre, The National Art Gallery, National Museum of Ireland, The National Concert Hall, Trinity College, Government Buildings and many other tourist attractions. With free Wi-Fi, free limited overnight parking mid week and free limited parking at the weekend, complementary free tea and coffee.

name: Double bedroom in newly refurbished apartement
description: Nice and quiet double bedroom in a newly refurbished apartment, 5 min walk to three arena, 20 min walk to city centre, plenty of public transport.

name: 4 Bedroom house available for Irish Golf Open
description: Our house is part of a small, quiet estate at the edge of the town of Lahinch. Most of the other houses are holiday homes. The living areas (kitchen and dining room, utility and sitting room) are on the ground floor with 1 double bedroom. There is a shower and toilet next to the bedroom so it can be used as an ensuite. Upstairs are 3 bedrooms - 1 kingsize bed and ensuite, 1 double bed, 1 double bed with a set of bunk beds. There is also a toilet.
neighborhoodOverview:
Golf and Surfing are among the main attractions in Lahinch. The beach has 2 kms. of fine golden sand with the championship links course is almost two-thirds surrounded by the beach and sea.
Its second golf course is also a fine 18 hole coastal course. Lahinch Golf Club and Golf Courses are World renowned and often described as the ‘Saint Andrews of Ireland'
The picturesque village of Liscannor and the renowned Cliffs of Moher are a short drive from our house.
The Burren landscape and the Aran Islands are all reachable by car as is the music capital of Clare - the village of Doolin.

After exploring Lahinch during the day, there is plenty of exploration to be done at night, with some excellent pubs in the area providing some really good music.

name: Clean Cozy room in safe area
description:
In the centre of the "Silicon Valley" of Europe, the apartment has two rooms and two bathrooms (one room and one bathroom is available for guests), with a short walk to all tourist sites and bars/restaurants. Your room is bright, clean, and quiet, with a double sized bed. High speed wifi and all amenities included.

The space
The cozy apartment has a feeling of home. You'll have a private room to yourself, and the other room is occupied by a working couple. Please note the bed is double-sized and the room is smaller than the picture looks (taken with a wide angle lens), so it's better suited for a single person or a couple. The room also contains some owner's belongings, though we keep them with minimum disturbance to your stay. The living room area can occasionally be a bit messy, but we are just a working couple not a professional hotel ;)

Guest access
Guest bedroom, main bathroom (shared), kitchen, living room, wifi, balcony. Additionally
neighborhoodOverview: Located in the "Silicon Valley" of Europe, this place is perfect for a professional on a short business trip, or a female traveller seeking safety and convenience.

name: Dooneen Apartment Miltown Malbay
description: Dooneen Apartment is a 2 Bedroom Self Catering  First Floor Apartment with Stunning Atlantic Sea Views. It is ideally located  a three minute walk from the Traditional Irish Music Town of Miltown Malbay and 5 minute drive from the beautiful beaches of  Spanish Point and the White Strand.
neighborhoodOverview: Miltown Malbay is a beautiful town conveniently situated in the mid west coast of Co. Clare. Tourist Attractions such as  the Loop Head Peninsula, the Burren National Park, the Cliffs of Moher,  Doolin,  Lahinch,  Kilkee are all within a 30 minute drive of the apartment. Miltown Malbay is famous for its traditional Irish Music as well as it's beautiful beaches - Spanish Point and the White Strand.

name: 4 Bed, 15 minutes from Trinity
description: Nestled in the shadow of the Aviva Stadium, this three-story house is a dream for a group staying in Dublin. 5 minutes walk from the RDS (Web Summit) and 15 minutes from Trinity College, the location can't be beaten. Spacious, comfortable and secure.

neighborhoodOverview:
You will be staying South of the river Liffey in the city centre, close to most attractions by foot, and with easy access to public transport. You’ll find yourself walking distance from Christchurch Cathedral, a magnificent structure and one of Dublin’s top tourist attractions. Dublin Castle, St Patrick's Cathedral and The Guinness Storehouse are also closeby landmarks worth visiting!

Once you’ve had your fill of historic wonders, you may wish to take a walk up Francis Street. Francis street is full to the brim of antique shops and bric a brac, for anyone who likes to discover old Irish hidden gems. At the other end of Francis Street you will arrive at a very trendy part of town, and should stop by to visit the Green Door Market to purchase fresh produce and delectable artisanal food. Nearby is the Fumbally Stables and Cafe, a local haunt for coffee lovers, sourdough bread bakers and farm-to-table enthusiasts. The Stables also hosts interesting courses, talks and yoga class

name: Luxury city centre large apartment in dublin 2
description:
High level finished apartment located in the heart of the city centre.
There is a double bedroom with lighted closet and terrace, large living room, fully equipped kitchen.
The apartment is surrounded by some of the best bars and restaurants in the city. It is located 10 minutes walking distance from all of the main attractions of the city including Grafton Street, Trinity College and Saint Stephen Green. It is a 10 minute drive/taxi from Grand Canal Dock and main tech companies.

Other things to note
The TV in the living room has Netflix activated only.

3-bedroom townhouse with 2 double beds & 2 single beds. Extra fold up beds available on request for guests in larger groups.

The location of this town house is absolutely ideal for visiting Dublin. It is on the south edge of the city centre beside the grand canal and close to some of the best bars and restaurants in the city. It is about 15 minutes walk from St Stephens green and Grafton street area and 25 minutes walk from temple bar.
When you don't fancy walking there are buses that pass and you're 5 mins walk to the tram.

Please be aware that as this is a townhouse in the city centre the kitchen/living area is compact enough, however it is perfect for cooking light meals and chilling out.

The house is over 4 floors and please be aware that is some stairs to get to upstairs bedrooms on 2nd and 3rd floor, however if anyone in your group has mobility issues there is an en suite bedroom on the ground floor and the first floor

description:
Lovely Double Room in the heart of Dublin for 2 guests with shared Bathroom & Kitchen.
Centrally located in an easily accessible area between the beautiful Merrion Square and Grand Canal Dock, this double bedroom has everything you need. Peace & quiet at night and a great location only 20mins walking from the city centre.

Guest access

Close to the Google HQ, Facebook HQ and Grand Canal Dock Area there is plenty to explore. Great Brunch Places, Cafes and Restaurants can be found right across the street or in the close surroundings. The city centre is only a nice 15-20min walk or 10min bus ride with the bus station located only 1 min from the house.

name: Slaveen
description:
Slaveen is a beautiful 3 bedroom house located 1km away from the bustling Main street and famous beach of Lahinch. This holiday home has the perfect location whether you want a quiet get away, or to take in all Lahinch has to offer.





The ground floor has an open fire in the living room, and a kitchen and dining room which lead onto a large conservatory and private back garden. There is a separate laundry room with washer and dryer. There is one double room ensuite on the ground floor.

name: Bright charming house close to 3 Arena
description:
Our newly renovated 2 1/2 bedroom house is truly charming. The space is bright and light whilst also retaining original features such as an exposed brick fireplace. There is also a pretty south facing garden complete with its own vine, apple and olive tree - perfect for a mid-morning coffee! Ideally located for 3Arena, Lansdowne Road (Aviva), Silicon Docks, IFSC and city centre.

The space
The space comfortably fits 4 adults. There is a large master bedroom, another double room and a small room off the master bedroom with a sofa bed.

The bathroom has a rainforest shower and a large bath.

The kitchen/dining area is the heart of the house, with its modern white units, farmhouse dining table and large windows and sliding door to the small sheltered south-facing garden. On a sunny morning, why not have your coffee al fresco beside our olive, apple and bay trees?

The living room is a cosy space and with lots of sheepskins, a gloriously
neighborhoodOverview: Ringsend is the best little community in Dublin! Red brick terraces, friendly people, wonderful cafes and restaurants...  All this, within only a 20 minute walk of the city centre (or a 5 minute bus journey) and a 10 minute walk of Sandymount Strand. It is a true Dublin experience! We are also just a 15 minute walk to the 3 Arena.

name: Bright 3 bedroom home in the heart of Dublin
description:
Right in the very heart of Dublin, just south of the river Liffey, this bright, cosy and well-appointed home is an ideal spot from which to base yourself while you enjoy the city.

There are three comfortable bedrooms, a bathroom, a handsome living area and a modern and well-equipped kitchen area.

There are also a number of interesting features in the property- such as a skylight in the attic bedroom (ideal for the stargazers among you!) and an attractive fireplace!

The space
The property is a semi-detached townhouse, ideal for families and small groups, though also a great option for those coming to Dublin for business, couples and even solo travellers!

There are three bedrooms, all of them are bright, with earthy, wooden accents. The attic bedroom comes with a skylight. Each of them is equipped with a double bed. The bathroom has a shower/bath combo, so you can have a nice soak after your time out and about if you so choose! The
neighborhoodOverview:
Just South of the River Liffey, you will be staying in the most convenient location Dublin has to offer, close to most attractions by foot, and with easy access to public transport (Bus, Luas, Dublin Bikes). You’ll be a short walk from Trinity College and its amazing library, The Book of Kells, and stone’s throw from O’Connell, Grafton Street and the buzzing temple bar.

You’ll be spoilt for great restaurants, pubs and cafes nearby in Temple Bar and South William Street.

Please take a look at the guidebook on my listing for recommended places to eat and drink in the area!

name: Luxury Holiday Home
description: My place is situated in the heart of the Burren, on the Wild Atlantic Way.  A wildly diverse ecosystem awaits any visitor to this corner of County Clare, dedicated a Special Area of Conservation by the EU. 2 km from Ballyvaughan and the sea, and surrounded by  Ireland’s 900 native plants species. You will love my place because of the comfy bed, the cosiness, the kitchen, and the views. Ideal for families (with kids), and big groups,  Aillwee Caves and Birds of Prey park right next door.

name: Cosy double En-suite with Shower
description:
Cosy double en-suite with shower in Dublin 4, less than 5 mins walk to the Aviva Stadium, 8 mins walk to the 3 Arena and 10 mins to the city centre.

We have a free parking space available for guests who choose to drive.

We have an abundance of cosy/quirky bars and restaurants on our doorstep but if that isn’t you, we are also located right beside Sandymount strand and Irishtown nature park which has beautiful walks all the way out to Poolbeg lighthouse (highly recommended).

name: Sonder *Monthly Discounts* 3BR Near Pearse Square Park
description:
Whether you are just getting away for the weekend or looking for an extended stay, we’re committed to creating comfortable experiences for our guests. We offer contact-free check-in and 24/7 virtual support which limits in-person interaction. In addition to following the guidance of the CDC and the World Health Organization, we’re partnering with sanitization experts at the Cleveland Clinic to ensure that all of our cleaning standards follow the advice of leaders in the field. We’ve put safety seals on high-touch items, stocked all spaces with complimentary hand sanitizer, and added social distancing signage in common areas. Each space is carefully designed and run by us, so you’ll always know what to expect.

- Digital check-in
- Professionally cleaned
- 24/7 virtual concierge via text, email, or phone
- Private all-in-one living spaces (ample work space)
- Utilities included (even for longer stays)
- Coffee, fresh towels, and bathroom essentials pro
neighborhoodOverview: Known as 'Silicon Docks', Docklands is filled with trendy eateries and premier coffee shops. This modern mecca provides endless entertainment through concerts, restaurants, and architecture. Travel back in time at The Irish Emigration museum, take a stroll through Pearse Square Park, or catch a live show at the stunning Bord Gáis Energy Theatre.

Bright & spacious, up in the clouds with panoramic views across Lahinch bay, nestled right beside the Cliffs of Moher :)

The space
Beside the Cliffs of Moher with rolling views all the way down to Lahinch Bay. Sunrises and sunsets. Local village of Liscannor, famous for fish, craic and slabs of stone. A nook of cosy to do as you please, chill, surf, read or frolic in the Burren.

Guest access
Entire house available to guests

Towels are also supplied with the room.

Guest access
Guest access is inclusive of master bedroom, private bathroom, all common areas and terrace.

name: Family holiday home close to beach
description:
Holiday home in the popular seaside town of Lahinch on the Wild Atlantic Way, renowned location for surfing and golf.
5 minutes walk to the beach and main street with restaurants & bars in abundance.
Plenty of attractions close by, Cliffs of Moher, Aliwee Caves, Doolin, The Burren, World famous Lahinch & Doonbeg Golf Courses and the popular wedding town of Ennistymon.
Easy drive to Shannon Airport, 50 minutes approx.

The space

Guest access
All areas of the house

name: Double Bedroom in Temple Bar City center
description:
Everything is green and all pubs are booming. Stay in our well located apartment where you can easily walk to the world famous Temple Bar (2 min), Trinity College (5 min),Dublin Castle (30 sec), Grafton Street, St.Patrick´s Cathedral, the Spire, the Jamenson Distilery and the Guinness Store(15 minutes) .Very close to bus stops, subway (Luas) ,train (Dart), supermarkets, coffee shops, etc. During the weekend there can be some noise from the pubs but we always have ear plugs for light sleepers :)

The space
Unique view at the beautiful City Hall and the city skyline. Lots of light and glass to enjoy the view. Easy access to everything the city has to offer. Forget taking a bus - enjoy everything on foot and save money for good food and drinks.
There might be construction noise going on.

Guest access
Guests will be able to access the kitchen and bathroom, but can also feel free to hang out in the living room with us.
neighborhoodOverview: Temple Bar! What is there to say? One of the most famous party districts ever. Lots of unique pubs, crazy nightlife, restaurants, Irish live music everywhere, and lots of fun loving tourists. From here you can easily get to the airport buy bus - the stop is almost in front of the building. Also, get to all tourist attractions on foot - the Guinness Factory - Harry Potters Library from the movies - Jameson Destillery - City Center - etc.

description:
4 km to Doolin 4 km to Lisdoonvarna. 9 km to cliffs of moher. 1km from Cliffs of Moher park and ride.

Regular ferry service to the Aran islands and sightseeing boat service to the cliffs from Doolin pier.

Local activities pitch and putt. Lahinch Golf course. Surfing lessons available, pony and horse riding, rock climbing, guided walking tours.

Complimentary breakfast served. Tea coffee, eggs with beans or ham, toast with jam or marmalade and yougert. Help to start you off for the day.

The space
Newly renovated cottage. Comfortable single bed. Use of sitting room with TV and solid fuel stove.

Guest access
Our guests are free to use the kitchen for tea or coffee. Washing machine iron and board is available. The use of our outdoor grill is available if you wish to cook some food the local butcher has excellent meats, fresh fish also available from our local supplier.
Our guests are welcome to be at home t
neighborhoodOverview:
Our place is on the main road to the cliffs of Moher. It's convenient to get to Doolin village and pier. Lisdoonvarna famous for its match makeing festival and spa wells is less than 4 km away.
Doolin Music house just a short walk away less than 5 mins. See "doolin music house" on line. We can arrange booking.

Should you wish to use public transport, the Luas city tram is a few minutes walk away and the Airlink757 Bus stops right across the street from the apartment. Dublin Bus options are just a few minutes walk away also.

description:
Modern Double Room with a comfortable King size bed and a luxurious private bathroom with bath. Crisp linen, toiletries, TV with Netflix, Nespresso Coffee Machine, etc.

The space

We aim at offering you a completely frictionless experience during your stay by inviting you to check in on your own whenever you want - no need to wait at the reception, nothing to bother with aside from enjoying your time

neighborhoodOverview:

Clarendon Street, Chatham Street and it’s adjacent streets offer the best shops, boutiques full of great and gifts ideas, independent art galleries, bars & award winning coffee bars, restaurants with the finest cuisine from all over the world with a twist of Irish, edgy cocktails clubs, tattoo parlours or fancy barber shops.

Within walking distance you have a choice of 12 pubs and a number of restaurants, local shops / supermarkets & launderette. We can provide you with a list of babysitters, taxi numbers & we will do all we can to ensure your stay is memorable.

The space
The apartment is newly decorated and has two bedrooms plus a double sofa bed in the kitchen / lounge. The Apartment is not suitable for parties or gatherings and is strictly non-smoking. The main bedroom is upstairs with a double and single bed, TV, DVD player, hairdryer and storage. The downstairs bedroom has a double bed and the lounge area has a very comfortable double sofa bed. Our apartment is within close walking distance of town yet outside of town givi
neighborhoodOverview: Miltown Malbay is the home of traditional Irish music so you are guaranteed a good night if its music or craic your after. The Cliffs of Moher are approx 30 minutes drive, so you won't be bored. If it's surfing, walking, kayaking, golf or relaxation and fabulous scenery this is the place for you.

description:

Please note that bedrooms are located over 5 floors & Albany House does not have a lift/elevator. Myself and the team at Albany House will be happy to advise you on how to make the most of your visit to Dublin.

* Each room has crisp white sheets and duvet

Our cabin has breathtaking views of the countryside with Liscannor bay in the distance and is a great base for visiting the Aran Islands, Cliffs Of Moher and the Burren. We are located 7km from the town of Ennistymon in the peaceful town land of Carrowduff.

The space
The cabin is situated on our 2.5 acre property and is a small (5m x 5.8m) but bright and cheery space. The cabin is heavily insulated in the walls, floor and ceiling so it is cosy and warm all year round and there are electric radiators for the cooler months. There is an en-suite shower room with a waterless eco composting toilet, electric shower and wash hand basin. The kitchen/living dining area has a kitchenete suitable for preparing basic meals with a portable electric 2 ring hob, fridg
neighborhoodOverview: We are situated within a 10-15min drive of the Cliffs Of Moher and all of the following villages, Doolin, Lahinch, Lisdoonvarna, Ennistymon and Liscannor.  Kilshanny House is our nearest pub just over 3km away. There are regular live traditional music nights in the pubs in Doolin through out the year.  Liscannor also offers pubs and restaurants as does Lahinch which is also famous for its beautiful surfing beach.  The town has many surf schools offering lessons suitable for all ages.  The town of Ennistymon is 7km away and  is a busy little rural town with supermarkets, banks, post office, grocery shops, pubs and restaurants.

Situated on the Wild Atlantic Way, boasting some of the most breathtaking scenery in Ireland, Doolin has something for everyone.

Located on the edge of the historic Burren in northwest County Clare, and within easy reach of the majestic Cliffs of Moher and the unique Aran Islands.

Doolin is the home of traditional Irish music. You can take a clifftop walk breathing in the crisp, salty Atlantic air while appreciating the beautiful wildflowers, explore the rugged landscape or go on an Atlantic cruise to appreciate the unique coastline from a different perspective.

name: Harans Main St Ennistymon Co. Clare
description:
Situated in the market town of Ennistymon, 35 mins drive from Shannon Airport. Harans is a step back in time, from where to experience the many attractions of the locality. Traditional music, cultural trails and the beauty of the Wild Atlantic Way

The space
Traditionally a house famous for gatherings of musicians, poets and writers and for celebrating our Irish speaking culture. Reminiscent of an 1950's home but with all the conveniences of today, you will be transported back to an era rich in space and time to slow down and unwind. Sit by a warm stove, read and relax in the upstairs parlor, cook and bake in our traditional kitchen.

Guest access
You are invited to enjoy every room in our home which offers space to enjoy a family gathering or to steal away to one of the the many quiet corners throughout the house to relax and connect with yourself.
neighborhoodOverview: One step from the front door and you are on the Main Street of Ennistymon where you can walk to our local shops and supermarket, enjoy the weekly Farmers Market and all offer quality and organic produce. Ennistymon has a library, art gallery and is a haven for many local and international artists and crafts people. You have many restaurants to choose from in the town and surrounding area to suit every taste and budget.  Local pubs offer the discerning drinker a vast collection of Irish and Scottish single malts to enjoy,  others offer traditional Irish music while another offers the services of our local matchmaker!  The Cascades are almost at your back door, Lahinch beach and Surf Schools and Golf Club 5 mins away. The Cliffs of Moher and the Burren and all the treasures of the Wild Atlantic Way are yours to enjoy. The town of Ennis also Limerick and Galway cities are all convenient and comfortable drives away.

Just a 20 minute walk from the city centre our cozy terraced cottage sits on a quiet cul-de-sac surrounded by a beautiful park, the River Liffey and Dublin Bay. Public transport is right around the corner and there is easy access to all the best amenities of Dublin.

The space
The available bedroom has a double bed and a single bunk. It also has a desk, closet and dresser, overhead light and reading lamps. The sitting room, kitchen and bathroom are on the ground floor. Our cottage has everything you need to enjoy your stay in Dublin.
As well as all the comforts of home there is also our lovable, slightly eccentric and a bit bossy dog, Clementine. She is a lurcher - a cross between a greyhound and an Irish wolfhound. She goes to doggy daycare Monday to Friday.

Guest access
I would be happy to show you around the neighbourhood and help get you acclimated.

Other things to note
The breezes from the river and se
neighborhoodOverview: Calm, relaxing with sea breezes and the best of the sunshine when we get it, Ringsend is a lovely inner city neighbourhood without the hassle of being in a big city.  There is local Tesco express supermarket, 3 pubs, a chipper, chinese take away and cafe as well as a Spar, 2 chemists, 3 charity shops a hairdresser and a barber.  Across the bridge there is a cinema and restaurants as well as a Starbucks.  Ringsend is a charming old neighbourhood, but at the same time it has the feel of a village.  Staying in Ringsend will give you the real Dublin experience.

The location is perfect and is only 1km from O'Connell Street and a host of other attractions. 800m from Connolly station for the dart and Luas is close by at Parnell Street.

Local amenities include Trinity College, Croke Park and a wide range of shops, bars and restaurants.

Transport links include Dublin bus services (123 from Summe
neighborhoodOverview: We are located just beside Croke Park and only 1km from O'Connell Street. If you fancy a nice brunch I would highly recomment the lovely food company in Drumcondra. The space
From a time when sailing ships berthed up to the bridge outside No 5, this is a house full of history and character, a house which has always been a bustling one.
Everyone who comes to stay enjoys spending time in the space. The house is old and crooked and has very much been allowed to be itself. The atmosphere is relaxed and informal, guests often have breakfast together around the dining room table which is our favourite thing to see.

Guest access

The small town of Malin is a two minute drive.

The space
The spacious, bright and modern 4 bedroom house is only a few minutes walk from the village. There are four spacious bedrooms, large living room, dinning room and modern kitchen.

The space

It has 2 bright double bedrooms both containing wardrobes and draws. Living area is of good size with lamps occasional tables freview tv dvd player and stereo . 3 seat sofa 2 seat sofa and armchair. Kitchen, living
Area and dining area are open space. Kitchen is fully equipped with kettle.fridge. microwave. Hob and oven.washing machine. All cooking utensils . There are double doors at rear of property leading to a small private patio for privacy if owners are on site. Table and chairs. Ideal space to bbq. The bathroom consists of toilet. Wash hand basin. Shower cubicle
neighborhoodOverview: The neighbourhood is of a rural setting. There are several houses within the vicinity. There is a corner shop aporox 10 minute walk away. A bar and restaurant and convenience store within 5km. Also the fabulous five finger strand beach with amazing sand dunes. You may be lucky enough to view the whales, dolphins and basking sharks in the summer months along side the pier.malinhead is approx 7km from our residence. This is irelands most northerly point and one of the 15 signature points on the wild atlantic way. Here you can visit by foot hells hole along the rugged cliffs.It is recognised as the best place on the ireland to view the northern lights. Incredible breathtaking views and walks are a must. The closest town is malin town then Cardonagh.

A refreshing ferry trip during summer takes you to Benone, Portrush or Portstewart. An 18 hole Golf course is only a short ‘drive’ away, while sandy beaches dot the area.

The space
- 3-Storey, modern, luxurious townhouse.

- Second floor panoramic living area, with stunning ocean view, well-equipped kitchen, constant hot water and heating (if required) modern soft furnishings and 50inch TV screen.

neighborhoodOverview: Friendly, relaxed and safe neighbourhood. The recent addition of an automated gate has added both aesthetically and in terms of privacy to the area. Close to the charming villages of Greencastle and Culdaff and the larger town of Moville, all of which offer wonderful bars, live music, eateries and entertainment. The region offers countless activities, for example, golf (Greencastle 18 hole course 500 yards away, Redcastle 9-hole 7 miles, Ballyliffen 2018 Irish Open, 30 min drive), horse riding, kayaking, surfing, body boarding, amusement centre, swimming pool, free public tennis courts, a local maritime museum, stunning walking trails, cycling routes for all abilities, not to mention the boundless expanse of sandy beaches.

description:

The space

The National Concert Hall and gorgeous Iveagh Gardens are about a 5 minute walk away.

Trinity College, St. Stephen's Green, Grafton Street, Dublin Castle, Christ Church and St. Patrick's Cathedral are all within easy walking distance (15-20 minutes max.)

The space

It is a lovely village, (has been described as the Williamsburg of Dublin), with the city centre on its doorstep. The house is very comfortable, bright and warm. The bedroom is a bright room with a very comfortable double bed with a quality new mattress and bookshelves. It's a really quiet room, perfect to chill out in and get a good night's sleep! We do not have any pets.

Guest acce

This is a spacious 2 double bedroom space with all mod cons, walk in shower and perfect for couples and families complete with pull out sofabed.

Kitchen: Fully equipped with everything that you need including: microwave, oven, hob, fridge/ freezer, toaster, kettle.
Living room: comfy sofa, open plan area with dining table, tv.
Bedroom1: small double
Bedroom2: queen size bed
Bathroom: large b
neighborhoodOverview:
Stoneybatter is located just 2 minutes to the river Liffey and is right beside the Luas museum stop.

Stoneybatter has been voted Irelands trendiest neighbourhood!

The Phoenix park is just beside you and the city center is only minutes away


Stoneybatter, is an up and coming neighbourhood of Dublin, on the Northside of the river Liffey, close to Pheonix Park and less than a 30 minute walk to the city centre. Every conceivable amenity is nearby including good restaurants, bars and shops on Manor Street and the Phoenix Park nearby provides a host of excellent facilities including: the Zoological Gardens, the Farmleigh estate and Ashtown Castle.

Please take a look at the guidebook on my listing for recommended places to eat and drink in the area!

name: Home alone (a lot) in a cute, cosy cottage
description:
Welcome to my 'higgledy piggledy' house; a terraced cottage built in the 1860s, on different levels. The cottage has recently been refurbished and it is bright, clean and very cosy.

The space
Beautiful, three-bedroom cottage in quiet street, close to Croke Park.

Guest takes one bedroom but has exclusive access to whole house (except owner's bedroom) and garden.

Arrangement with friend to let guest into the house.

I'll correspond only by email unless I happen to be home. Contact will be with a friend.

Great neighbours and quiet street - except on (GAA) match days when it is colourfully, wonderfully atmospheric as people head up the street to the match in Croke Park.

The 123 bus runs from the end of the road. DART (Connolly St.) within 15 minute walk O'Connell Street just a few minutes' walk

As I am not around, I am really looking for longer term guests who would like to stay for months at a time.
neighborhoodOverview: My cute three-bedroom cottage is located on a quiet, tree-lined street with roadside parking and great neighbours. It is in the shadow (not literally!) of Croke Park and a short walk from O'Connell Street, the IFSC and East Point.

name: Cozy room in Smithfield
description:
The room is in the nice area of Smithfield close to the city center and temple bar. It’s really quiet and the flat is big and light.
Everything is nearby like supermarkets some restaurants which i can really recommend.
It’s perfect for some days in Dublin to see the best of the city but still sleep in a nice, quiet area.
If you need any recommendations regarding pubs, clubs or something else I like to help you.

Guest access
You will have your own room which you can lock. There are no pets or anything else. You can use as well the living room, kitchen and bathroom. Everything will be shared with my flatmate.
neighborhoodOverview: It’s a really quiet and nice area with a lot of restaurants and supermarkets. But within waking distance to the temple bar.

description:
Newly refurbished town centre apartment set up for guests comfort and convenience. Modern sparkling clean kitchen and shower room. All new beds and bedding. Funky living space ideal for couples, small groups or families. Host lives near by and will greet you on arrival. Free parking and walking distance to all town . Ideal base for wedding guests , golfers and Wild Atlantic Way visitors.
Also available we have a 5 bedroom bungalow which sleeps 8 ,
https://www.airbnb.ie/rooms/26943314?s=51

The space
A cool chillout little space in the heart of urban living ideally located in this busy market town in central Inishowen , a very unique space .

Guest access
All ground floor space .

Other things to note
There is private parking to rear of property , park up on arrival and then relax .
neighborhoodOverview:
A townhouse apartment on one of the main streets in our small town , close to cafes resturants bars shops churches and all amenities .
Central to inishowen and all its mystery and beauty along the wild atlantic way . Ballyliffen golf complex a mere 10 minutes drive . Malin head 20mins , Culdaff 15 mins .........

name: Modern & Central 1 Bed Apt in Dublin 1!
description:
Modern, one bedroom apartment located in the very heart of Dublin. This apartment is less than 10 minutes from O'Connell Street, making this a great base for those looking to explore the city by foot.

The apartment is spacious and comfortable with lots of natural light. It's a perfect base for solo adventurers, couples, or business travellers looking to stay in the city centre.

The space
Building:
Modern development in the city centre
Elevator in the building

Amenities:
High thread-count bed linen and towels
We meet guests at the entrance.
Fully-equipped kitchen

Kitchen & Living room:
Fridge
Oven
Microwave
Kettle
Washing machine (no drier)
TV

Bedroom:
King size bed
Ample storage space

Bathroom:
Separate bathroom with bath and shower available
