Guest access
Guests will have access to
neighborhoodOverview:
ust North of the River Liffey and a short walk from historic O'Connell Street, this is the very heart of the city centre and the perfect location for anyone wishing to explore the city by foot.

One of Dublin’s main shopping hubs is O'Connell Street (and its tributary, the ever-busy Henry Street), which culminates in a spearhead of excellent museums dotted around Parnell Square (most notably the Hugh Lane Gallery). To the west of here is the up-and-coming Smithfield and, further still, the vast Phoenix Park (also home to Dublin Zoo) while just across the bridge to the south is the formidable campus of Trinity College, with its ancient claim to fame in pride of place in the Old Library & Book of Kells.

You have everything at your doorstep in the city centre and there's an exciting mix of cultures and ideas to cater for every whim you might have.

Please take a look at the guidebook on my listing for recommended places to eat and drink in the area!

name: Spencer Dock, my house is your house.
description:
Area around: Fashionable restaurants, bars and shops and an expansive
linear park surround it. It has direct access to the south side of the city via the New Macken St Bridge. It is well serviced by LUAS, rail, bus, air link [to the airport] and water taxis.

name: The Market Square Nook moville co. Donegal
description: This apartment sleeps 6 people a 7th person could sleel on the couch as its big enough.I have decorated it to feel like a home from home. It's cosy  with lots of natural light, spacious & soft colours . The apartment is in the middle of the town right beside all local pubs shops restaurant's etc. & 2 min  from our beautiful coastal shore walk and play park and 2 mins from Inish Adventures.

name: The Shannon Suite-Historic City Centre Apartment
description:
This beautiful 2 bedroom apartment and is a wonderful opportunity to experience Georgian Dublin in all its splendour. The living rooms are filled with light from the large Georgian windows, with detailed cornicing adding an air of formal refinement to the rooms. The comfortable furnishings give the place a homely feel, making it a magnificent setting to relax and enjoy your stay in Dublin.

The space
This building was first constructed in 1755 and has just been totally refurbished. This apartment is a fantastic mix of beautiful Georgian architecture while having all the modern conveniences available

Guest access
You will have access to the full apartment and common areas of the building
neighborhoodOverview: The Henrietta Suites are located on Henrietta Street, right in the heart of the city and just a 10 minute walk to Trinity College and Temple Bar. The shopping district of Henry Street is just around the corner and there are excellent restaurants such as The Winding Stair nearby. It's central location makes it an ideal place to explore the city while staying in one of Dublin's finest examples of Georgian living.

name: Traditional, modern family home
description:
We are eager to host you in our home.
Newly renovated kitchen & bathrooms, comfortable beds, and underfloor heating will ensure this base for your Dublin trip is as relaxed as possible.
More than a house, we pride ourselves on a positive & friendly hosting experience.
We will help you get your bearings and go the extra mile for you.
You'll be on leafy Clonliffe Road, just minutes to Croke Park & 15 minute walk to O’Connell St.
Buses to city centre & Dublin Airport within easy walking distance

The space
We have made every effort to ensure the house is warm and comfortable.
There is underfloor heating in the main living room and the bathrooms, we have solar-powered constant hot water with great water pressure.
The living room floods with sunlight in the morning and the kitchen will always be stocked with your needs for coffee and tea.
This home has been in our family for generations; it is loved, and we want you to feel at ho
neighborhoodOverview:
What you will find locally is all the shops and takeaway food you might need, but also some great local pubs.
Gaffney's, which is a 5 minute walk is - by ur reckoning - one of Dublin's best kept secrets
Gaffney's link - goo.gl/d2khPS
The house is next to an old burial ground, the Suicide Plot, which was the inspiration for Bram Stoker's Dracula
"Ballybough Cemetery, known as the "suicide plot", which was used for suicide victims, robbers and highwaymen, through whose corpses' hearts wooden stakes were driven"
Suicide Plot link - goo.gl/Duv8GM

We are one street from Croke Park, the beating heart of Ireland's unique GAA sporting heritage. The onsite museum is a treasure.
Croke Park museum link - goo.gl/aX5ytp

name: The Wee House
description: Situated on Inishowen head and part of the Wild Atlantic Way the "Wee House" is a totally refurbished detached studio ideal for 2 people. It over looks magnificent Lough Foyle and Greencastle Golf Club and is ideally located for those who like to walk, cycle, fish or golf. There are several stunning beaches in the surrounding area. It is 4km from the nearest village of Greencastle. In the summer months a ferry runs from Greencastle across to the Antrim coast.

name: Family-Friendly Victorian Townhouse in an Ancient Square
description: Step through a front door with stained-glass panels and immediately feel the warm vibe of timber floors, richly coloured paintwork, and an original fireplace. Modern updates abound, including a marble-lined bathroom and contemporary eat-in kitchen.
neighborhoodOverview: The house is located in the oldest square in Dublin, close to Smithfield Market. A children's playground is nearby, and it's a minute's walk to the Liffey River. The city centre and most attractions are within walking distance.

name: Clean Room in a Cozy House + Centrally Located!
description:
A smaller sized but clean room in a Cozy house in a prime location, less than 10 minutes walk from the city centre or the River Liffey. In a quiet and safe area. We have a cozy living room with a smart tv (Netflix, Amazon Video) and loads of board games for you to use. We also have a kitchen which you are more than welcome to make use of, and maybe score yourself dinner if one of us is cooking! There is a toilet upstairs and a shared shower downstairs.

Guest access
All Access :)

name: Loft Apartment Junior
description:
Sleeping up to 11 people, this spacious apartment is right in the heart of Dublin, in Dublin 1. A five minute walk from O'Connell street, Dublin's premier shopping and entertainment district.
It's a smaller section of our larger Georgian Loft Apartment, also available on Airbnb

name: Townhouse @ the Fort Greencastle Co Donegal
description:
The Fort Townhouse is in Greencastle Co Donegal with spectacular views of Lough Foyle and the Antrim Coast. This stunning home is only a few minutes walk from the heart of the village and the beautiful beach at Stroove. In addition to this the City of Derry is only 35km from Greencastle. This home is perfect due to the quiet and relaxed atmosphere created by the high ceilings, unique views and the cosy bespoke interiors, perfect for couples and families with children

The space
The Space:
• Luxury 3-storey townhouse with sea-facing balcony
• Ground floor: spacious hall area, 2 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms (one is an en suite washroom near the back door – perfect to access after a day at the beach!)
• Middle floor: open-plan area – spacious kitchen and dining, large lounge area with TV and spectacular views, access to lounge area on balcony
• Top floor: loft style master bedroom with walk in wardrobe and en suite
• Parking space for 2 cars
neighborhoodOverview:
We are steps away from the centre of Greencastle with its bars, cafe/shop, Award winning restaurant, Maritime Museum and observatory and Fresh Fish Shop

Traveling from the village to the town of Moville is 5 km for larger shops and bars
Derry City in Northern Ireland is 35 km where you can explore the city walls and a variety of Museums

In Greencastle and surrounding area there are many fine beaches at Shrove and Kinnagoe Bay
Travellers can begin there tour of the Wild Altlantic Way in Greencastle

name: Private Room in modern apt in the heart of Dublin
description:
This is a bright, spacious and quiet apartment located in the financial district of the city centre. It is the perfect location for anyone travelling either for business or for pleasure. It is located on the door step to the main shopping streets and the amazing food scene that Dublin is currently experiencing. Every part of Dublin is unique and offers something for everyone. Staying in the centre of the city will make your experience even better.

The space
We both live in the apartment and only rent it when we want so everything in it is personal and has a very homely feel. We ask that you do respect our place as it is our home.

Guest access
Depending on the length of your stay we may be able to accommodate a car parking space but we will need advanced notice.

Other things to note
Google maps sometimes brings you to the wrong gate that can't be opened so be sure to read the instructions we send you after your booking
neighborhoodOverview: The IFSC is the financial district of Dublin. The area has seen massive growth since the early 2000s. It's home to some of the largest companies in the world (KPMG, Morgan Stanley and Hubspot to name a few. The beauty of being in the centre of Dublin is that you're never more then 10 minutes from where you want to go. This is a perfect apartment for both personal travellers and business travellers.

name: Biddy Ban's Luxury Self-Catering King "Natasha"
description:
Biddy Ban's is a newly renovated farmhouse split into 4 luxury self catering apartments in the beautiful, rugged and scenic area of Malin Head, Co. Donegal.

This listing is for the "Natasha" King Suite. This apartment is situated on the ground floor of the house. It is rooms are furnished with a king size bed and mattress of a minimum of 12 inches/300mm in depth.

Each apartment has mixed the convenience of a self-catering, the cosiness of a B&B and the style of the most luxurious hotel rooms.

The space
Biddy Ban’s is the result of the total refurbishment of a 2 storey farmhouse in the village of Culoort. The property is circa 150 years old and was in a poor state of repair when we acquired it at the end of 2017, having lay empty for nearly 5 years. However after many hours of hard work by some very skilled, local tradesmen, we have given this wonderful old building a new lease of life. It has now been transformed into 4 luxury self catering
neighborhoodOverview: Some of the most spectacular, unspoiled scenery you're likely to see in the whole of Ireland.

description:
Hello there :)
Our space is a student/tourist vibe, located in the city center, we are just 5 min walking from IFSC and Docklands, where you can find Supermarkets, Centra, Spar, pharmacies with a short walk of 5 min or even less, Great choice in terms of location and value you will be very welcome here. There are 3 beds in the room, check prices and special offer for more than 1 guest =)
Come stay with us !

The space
A spacious triple room that comprises 3 single beds available, you will share with 2 more people or no, you will have access a shared bathroom and toilet which is clean with essentials included. The kitchen is fully equipped for meal preparation, its small but comfy.
Mixed room (Male and Female)

neighborhoodOverview: It's city center atmosphere!

name: Stylish, Cosy Room, in Trendy City Apartment
description:
Contemporary, clean apartment with all mod cons. Complete with views of the Liffey from the living room, and views of the Guinness Factory from the bedroom, it will make you feel like a local during your stay.

Access to 747 Airport Bus as well as Red Line Luas stops (the latter of which runs direct to the 3 Arena) are a short 5 minute walk from the property.

The space
A bright and airy, fashionable and clean room, with a comfortable double bed, wardrobe and added storage facilities. Wi-Fi available.

Guest access
Guests have full access to the living areas.
neighborhoodOverview:
The property straddles the line between The Liberties in Dublin 8 and Smithfield in Dublin 7, with a mere walk over Mellowes Bridge to the latter. Both areas are dynamic city neighbourhoods bursting with vibrant community life, and 21st century innovation.

The Liberties boasting the cool chic of District 8 nightclub, The Thomas House, The Beer Market and Teeling Distillery as well as the old guard of The Brazen Head (oldest pub in Dublin, and a 2 minute stroll from the premises), The Guinness Storehouse, Kilmainham Gaol, the Modern Art Museum, Christchurch and St Patricks Cathedral. Not to mention the innovative Digital Hub.

Smithfield hosts a similar mix of the uber trendy and the oldschool in Dice Bar, The Lighthouse Cinema, Frank Ryans, Wuff Restaurant, The Cobblestone, Oscars Smithfield, Index Nightclub, Fish Shop, My Meat Wagon, Thundercut Alley, L Mulligan grocer and more, with an ever growing list of hipster cafes, artisan shopping and pop-ups opening on a

name: Sliabh Dual
description:
From this perfect touring base you can visit two unspoiled beaches within a 5 minute drive. In addition to this Inishowen also boasts numerous beaches across the coastal region. If golf is your game of choice there is a broad range of golf clubs and resorts including a championship links golf course at Ballyliffin 10 minutes away.

The space
Sliabh Dual translated is "Mountain Strand" which accurately describes this new luxurious cottage which hosts spectacular views over Malin and Trawbreaga Bay, nestled comfortably within the scenic Inishowen mountains along the Wild Atlantic Way.

Guest access
Your stay at Sliabh Dual guarantees endless opportunities for a tailor-made holiday including rambling on the 20 acres of private land, mountain hikes, walking trails, horse riding, cycling, deep sea fishing, salmon rivers, surfing and even scuba diving on German U-boats off Ireland's most northerly point in Malin Head.

Other things to
neighborhoodOverview:
Every season hosts a range of action packed local activities. In the Spring time the St Patrick's Day Parade's kick off the start of spring and Culdaff exercises a Climbfest. The summer months proudly bring numerous community wide Inishowen family Festivals, Music Concerts and Regattas. The Autumn brings the Charles Macklin Festival and in the Winter Santa comes to Inishowen and stays in the Isle of Doagh which is a truly magical experience for people of all ages!

If you are feeling adventurous why not take the car ferry across the scenic Lough Foyle and visit the stunning Antrim Coast with its many alluring tourist features including the Giants Causeway, Carrick-a-Rede rope bridge and the historic Bushmills Whiskey Distillery. The gateway to the Antrim Coast is only a 40 minute's drive from Sliabh Dual.

name: Bright airy one bed apartment in Smithfield
description:
This bright apartment is a great option for a singleton or a couple working in Dublin or visiting as tourists. Ideally located close to the centre, it is within a stones throw of the Jameson Distillery, St Michan's Crypts, Collins Barracks Museum and the Phoenix Park. The legal district and financial district (IFSC) are all nearby or located along the Luas tram line. Also nearby are the Guinness Storehouse, Kilmainham Gaol/Jail, Temple Bar, Trinity College Dublin and Grafton Street.

The space
The apartment is quiet, bright and clean. It's bang in the centre of Smithfield, around the corner from the plaza. Stoneybatter is equidistant away so there are plenty of options for shops, restaurants and cafes. Most tourist attractions are well within walking distance as is the city centre. It's also very well connected by public transport with the train stations, tram and bus stops nearby.

Guest access
You will have the entire place to yourself so y
neighborhoodOverview: The neighbourhood has an eclectic mix of local Dubliners, young professionals and beard-donning hipsters. Smithfield offers a range of busy bars including the Cobblestone (which is famous for its nightly Irish traditional music), the Dice Bar, (for its rock music and dive-feel), Frank Ryans (a long-standing local pub) and Mulligans, an award-winning gastro pub. The nearby Lighthouse Cinema features art-house films and is a great way to relax away from the hustle and bustle while an array of local restaurants to choose from including Cotto (amazing pizzas) and Fish Shop (amaaaazing fish!) won't leave you hungry.

name: Bright double room/shower in Dublin City Center

The flat will hold 3. The

Some bars are really close such as The Mission Bar, Dice Bar, Frank Ryan's
neighborhoodOverview: It's a quiet neighbourhood with many options for transport. Pretty much safe area.

description:
My place is 5 minutes to the city centre, 10 minutes to the Temple bar and The Jameson distillery is 2 minutes walking.
If you don't feel like walking you can always take the Dublin bike, there is a bike station in front of our apartment. The bus stop is at the entrance and the Tram 5-minute walk away.

The living room is very cosy and you'll feel at home. Since I work during the week you'll only have to share it during the evening and in the weekend ☺

The space
There is a single bed and an airbed in the living room. You can watch some tv, play on our PlayStation or cook a nice meal in our kitchen.

Usually, after 10 pm I don't use the living room.

Guest access
There is no access to the bedroom, please don't try to open this.

You will have access to the bathroom, the living room and the kitchen.

name: Barney's Lodge
description:
Barney's Lodge, Glacknabrade, is situated at the end of a private lane, just off the road to Blackmountain Road to Malin Head, 3 kms from the village of Malin. The cottage is newly refurbished throughout. We enjoy welcoming visitors to this beautiful part of Donegal, thus, we are looking forward to meeting guests from all backgrounds and corners of the globe for a real Donegal welcome.

The space
If you are looking for a space where you can hear the birds sing as you wake, watch the cows and sheep graze as you look out the window, and hear the sound of the stream running as you venture outside in the morning, then Barney's Lodge is the place to be. The private, peaceful and scenic setting of the cottage will ensure that you have a relaxing stay.

Guest access
Guests can access the entire cottage. Along with the three bedrooms and one bathroom, there is a compact kitchen, a large sitting/dining room with a solid fuel stove with back boiler, an
neighborhoodOverview: Malin, the nearest village, is on the Wild Atlantic Way and we have seen a large influx of visitors to view the stunning scenery of the Inishowen Peninsula in recent years. The cottage is 12kms from Bamba's Crown, Malin Head, Ireland's most Northerly Point. Scenes from the most recent Star Wars Film, The Last Jedi, were filmed there in 2016. Depending on the time of your visit, you may also be lucky enough to see the Northern Lights, or get a glimpse of the dolphins as they dance towards the pier in Malin Head.

This is a beautiful apartment just steps away from Temple Bar, and right beside the Ha’Penny Bridge. It is a fantastic location and apartment. Accommodating up to 4 people, the flat is relaxing, comfortable and quiet. Walk outside the front though, and you are instantly immersed in the atmosphere of Dublin’s city-centre.

The space
Ideally located, nicely decorated, clean, and quiet – this is the perfect city-centre apartment. The flat is located on Liffey Street, just steps away from the Ha’Penny Bridge, Temple Bar, O’Connell Street, and many other main attractions. This is a newly refurbished apartment, with a spacious living area – perfect for two extra guests, as it has a comfortable double sofa bed. With a lovely bathroom, a fully equipped kitchen, and a cosy bedroom fitted with a double bed – you are sure to enjoy an exciting experience in Dublin city, and a tranquil one in the apartment.

Guest access

The neighbourhood is full of areas for you to shop, eat, drink, and sightsee.

description:
Rockydale is located on a gentle slope overlooking Lough Foyle on the eastern side of the Inishowen Peninsula. It is close to the Redcastle Hotel.
The house enjoys spectacular views overlooking Lough Foyle and the surrounding countryside.
Inishowen Peninsula

description: This room is available in a beautiful, cozy two bedroom apartment in the very convenient Point Village area. Immediately next door to the 3Arena and the Gibson Hotel, the view of the Dublin Port and iconic Poolbeg Towers is one that needs to be seen to be believed.

description:
Cozy private room in a big and beautiful shared house.
This accommodation is perfect for travelers or students who needs a temporary place to stay.
We are at only 15/20 minutes by foot from the city center or for those who doesn't like to walk there is a bus stop less than 1 minute from the house, with buses leaving every 10 minutes, also there is a Luas stop (tram/light rail system) at 2 minutes.

The space
The accommodation consists of a big, bright and comfortable living area also a kitchen, a restroom, a bathroom and others guest's room.
The kitchen and dining space is cosy . It has all the appliances you could need. An oven, sink, fridge, microwave, kettle and toaster. It has a washing machine and dryer that you can use to wash your clothes and dry. It has a big table and also a small counter for extra convenience when dining. You have access to all our pots and pans, so you are free to cook and prepare your own food as well as eat out nearby

description: Lugares de interés: 101 Talbot St. Te va a encantar mi lugar debido a la ubicación, la gente y el barrio. Mi alojamiento es bueno para parejas y mascotas.

name: Cromlech Cottage
description:
On The Wild Atlantic Way

Welcome to Cromlech Cottage.
Our cottage Sleeps five guests and is very central to all the beautiful places in Narin and Portnoo.
There is a lovely solid fuel stove to keep you warm on the cold evenings along with oil central heating .

We are about 15 mins walk from the city and the same from the sea. We love it here, we hope you do too.

The space

The downstairs is all open plan and we have injected our love of colour and mid century furniture.

There’s a lovely log fire for a cold night and i love to cook so you’ve a fully equipped kitchen.

Up the road right and keep right is the spectacular headland of Bloody Foreland (named for the crimson colour of the rocks at sunset on the sea)

Visit Horn Head and Glenveagh national park, with 16000 hectares of mountains, lakes, wood and bog. Glenveagh contains the largest red dear population in Europe. The castle and gardens are worth visiting alone for a breathtaking insight to times gone by.

Visit Dunlewey Lakeside Centre- facilities include restaurant, tea-room, craft shop, adventure play area, pets and animals, story telling, boat trips on Dunlewey lake, guided tours and weaving demonstrations

Take a day trip to Tory Island or Gola Island. The ferry service is available from Bunbeg or Magheraroarty harbour several times a day.

Climb Errigal and Muckish. Mount Errigal is the highest mountain in Donegal with more fun descending than climbing.

Fishing, Golf, Traditional Music 1 mile. Walking. Horse riding, Swimming Pool 3 mile

The space

The spacious living area is perfect for relaxing after a day of activity where you can kick back on the comfy couch and Netflix and chill. The bedroom has a super-king size bed and a large en-suite bathroom with a walk-in shower.

The flat is located on Main Street in Dunfanaghy, directly across from the
neighborhoodOverview: Dunfanaghy is a must for any holiday maker cruising along Donegal’s Wild Atlantic Way. Greater Dunfanaghy is home to artisan sourdough pizza, a yoga studio, more than one surf school, locally roasted coffee, clothing boutiques, art galleries, multiple restaurants and a spa with views like no other. For the outdoor adventurer, you can hike for hours, bike through the windy back roads, ride horses, golf, surf and so much more.

The master bedroom also has an ensuite bathroom and access to a small private balcony. The apartment is professionally cleaned, and provides hotel-quality high thread-count bed linen and towels, as well as having a fully equipped kitchen. The living area leads onto a large balcony with outdoor seating and a great view of north Dublin city centre. The living area has a comfortable sofa as well as two armchairs, and a TV. The kitchen also has a dishwasher and washing machine.

Guest access

neighborhoodOverview:
Just North of the River Liffey and a short walk from historic O'Connell Street, this is the very heart of the city centre and the perfect location for anyone wishing to explore the city by foot.

One of Dublin’s main shopping hubs is O'Connell Street (and its tributary, the ever-busy Henry Street), which culminates in a spearhead of excellent museums dotted around Parnell Square (most notably the Hugh Lane Gallery). To the west of here is the up-and-coming Smithfield and, further still, the vast Phoenix Park (also home to Dublin Zoo) while just across the bridge to the south is the formidable campus of Trinity College, with its ancient claim to fame in pride of place in the Old Library & Book of Kells.

You have everything at your doorstep in the city centre and there's an exciting mix of cultures and ideas to cater for every whim you might have.

Please take a look at the guidebook on my listing for recommended places to eat and drink in the area!

Forming part of the Wild Atlantic Way, the majestic Horn Head, with its attractive and rugged coastline is a 5 minute drive from the property. Ardara is a designated Heritage Town on the Wild Atlantic Way and also a well known centre for the manufacture of Donegal homespun tweeds. The area boasts a thriving tourist trade and social scene, and has been awarded The Irish Times (National Newspaper) 'Best Village to Live In 2014'. Traditional music is to be heard any night of the week during the summer months in many of the local pubs and one cannot speak of Ardara without a mention of the renowned "Nancy's Bar" where the seafood (and the company) is second to none, being one of thirteen 'Good Food Taverns' in the Donegal area and winner of Georgina Campbell's 'Pub of the Year 2013' amongst many other accolades.
For fine dining visit Woodhill House, an historic coastal manor house dating back in parts to the 17th century. The house overlooks the beautiful Donegal Highlands is set in its own gro

It contains the entire north side of Dublin Docklands and includes the International Financial Services Centre, Spencer Dock, and further east the main part of Dublin Port. It’s therefore a great base if you’re travelling here on Business.

Dublin Docklands is fast becoming a must-see destination on any sightseeing trip of the capital. From stunning modern architecture to historic buildings, from art galleries to river trips - Docklands has it all. Best thing is that it's only a short stroll from the city centre so you can be here from O'Connell Street in just a few minutes.

There are two bedrooms upstairs, one has a king size bed and the second is a sofa bed.

Stoneybatter is a great neighbourhood in central Dublin. It is a vibrant and friendly neighbourhood village right in the city.  It is a 15 min walk to O'Connell Street and 20 mins to Trinity College. Everything is on your doorstep.

Getting around
As everything is so close by you can walk everywhere.
Local buses for the area are 39, 39a, 37 and 70, 46A

description:
Portsalon Pier - Beach House has a truly idyllic setting in the wonderful beach and golf resort of Portsalon on the Fanad Peninsula. This fine self-catering accommodation overlooks Portsalon Harbour which has a small sheltered golden beach with adjacent rock pools. A few steps from the patio door and you are on the sand. Just beyond the rocks is the vast expanse of golden sands of the Blue Flag Beach of Portsalon. The superb Portsalon Golf Club is a few minutes walk from your front door.

The space
Optional continental breakfast option is available upon request. A choice of a selection of fruit, yogurt, pastries, juice, meats and/or cheeses. Starting from €7.50 per person.

New and improved FTTH broadband and wifi installed August 2020. There also isn't a TV in the house.

Please check seasonal accommodation pricing.

Season - Weekly Pricing
Saturday - Saturday preferred.

neighborhoodOverview:
For food and drink we would recommend the Stores Bar, Pier Restaurant or Golf Club in Portsalon, or The Narrow Quarter in Kerrykeel. Please note that these businesses are run independently of the accommodation we manage, so for updated opening times, menus or any further information; we advise contacting the businesses directly.

Portsalon beach is outside your door and window.

Eco Atlantic Adventures do Kayaking activities and tours from the pier in Portsalon. I would highly recommend doing one of these activities if you can during your stay.

Portsalon Golf Club is a 5 min walk if you would like a round of golf and food afterwards. The Narrow Quarter in Kerrykeel is a 10 min drive, but well worth it, for breakfast, lunch or dinner.

Laid-back cafes serve artisanal coffee, while sleek restaurants feature creative global cuisine and modern takes on traditional food. Nightlife can mean lively folk music at a pub or casual drinks at a craft-beer bar. The Jameson Distillery Bow Street offers tours and tastings for those interested in Irish whiskey.
Tipperary House is the perfect starting point for whatever brings you to Dublin.

The space

There is a large bright living room with flat screen tv and an open fireplace. An archway leads into the kitchen and dining area which is fully equipped for a self catering holiday. A separate utility area is adjacent to the kitchen. On the ground floor there is a double bedroom ensuite with bath. There are 2 bedrooms on the first floor ,each with a double and single bed. A shower room is also located on the first floor. O
neighborhoodOverview: Rathmullan itself is a mecca for watersports enthusiasts. Swimming, sailing, kayaking and stand-up paddle boarding are popular local activities. There are two charter boats based at the pier that offer sea angling trips and also sightseeing trips on Lough Swilly. Fishing from the pier is also popular. Fine dining can be enjoyed at the Cook and Gardener Restaurant in Rathmullan House. Also at Rathmullan House is the Taproom in the Cellar Bar which specialises in Pizzas and local Kinnegar Beers. The village is blessed with two other fine restaurants- Belles Kitchen and An Bonnan Bui The scenic 9 hole Otway Golf Club is 4km away and the superb Portsalon golf Club is a 25 minute drive. Rathmullan is located along Irelands Wild Atlantic Way and there are some spectacular coastal drives in the region around the village. The space

The kitchen has a 5 gas hob and double electric Oven and has pots, pans, glasses, crockery and cutlery that will cater for all your n
neighborhoodOverview:
Our house is located in the lovely neighbourhood of Drumcondra, where old Victorian redbricks like ours are ubiquitous - a lovely leafy area to wander around.

Coffee and food: The immediate vicinity has some great coffee shops (Nelly’s, The Duck, Bread and Butter) and a fantastic inexpensive Middle Eastern (Shouk) 3 mins walk away - the latter was in the Irish times top 100 restaurants for 2019. The Lovely Food Company is a great spot for brunch (5 mins walk) and if you’re feeling energetic the fabulous Cloud Cafe is 15 mins walk to the opposite side of Croke Park).

The walk to upper Drumcondra is along a vast and beautiful tree lined avenue towards some more great restaurants including our favourite casual spot for Thai San Sab. The very local pub is McGrath’s where the Guinness and the welcome is top notch and within 10-15 mins you’ve got Kennedy’s, Fagan’s (Bertie Ahern’s favourite local) and beside the canal in the other direction is the Bald Eagle, Hedigans

Plus it’s an area of the inner city rich in history, close to lively Stoneybatter and handy for the Phoenix Park.

There are two bedrooms (each has a double bed), and there's a very comfortable double sofa-bed in the living room. In all, the apartment can sleep six adults. Bear in mind, though, that there's only one bathroom.

name: Beautiful modern apartment close to city centre
description:
Beautiful modern apartment, with fully equipped kitchen and private bathroom. Large balcony and roof terrace with views of Pheonix Park. Situated in a cool part of the city, next to Kilmainham Gaol, museums, Hilton hotel and Menorial and Pheonix park.
Only 7 minutes by car to the city centre, 13 minutes by bus to Temple bar and Trinity college.
Walking distance to pubs, cafe, restaurants and the Guiness Factory.

name: Lux Double Room  Great location
description:
My place is located in a beautiful historical building. It has been completely renovated to a high standard though it still retains its originality and charm.
Comfortable private double bedroom at just 25 minutes walking from the city centre. Enjoy your stay with easy access to all amenities and touristic spots nearby!
My aim is to make your stay in Dublin as comfortable and enjoyable as possible while providing a high-quality service at a budget price.

name: Trohanny Cottage Authentic Irish Thatched cottage
description:
Rare opportunity to stay in a pre-1800's listed traditional Irish Thatched stone cottage and farmstead, less than one hour from Dublin.
A beautifully restored piece of Irish history but with all the modern benefits, cosy and welcoming with a very special atmosphere.
We specialise in 1-3 night stays for old fashioned romance, rest, relaxation, and to re-charge!
Read our reviews to hear why our guests return..
A little piece of heaven awaits
Follow our story online @trohannycottage/trohanny.ie

The space
Trohanny cottage is a rare gem. You can enjoy the stunning Irish countryside and the atmosphere of an old thatched building with whitewashed stone walls, old beams, original ingle-nook fireplace, turf fire, genuine antique pieces of furniture yet with the comfort of underfloor heating, clean cosy spaces with quality furnishings, treats in your fridge, fuel for your fire, candles for every corner and an extra deep enamel bath with luxurious
neighborhoodOverview:
Trohanny is a few kms(8km) from the village of Moynalty, a pretty little place which is well renowned for it's steam threshing festival in August and for also winning numerous 'Tidy town' awards over the years.
We are just 15 mins to the historic town of Kells and 35 mins from the larger town of Navan, less than one hour to Dublin.
Also within easy reach of The Boyne Valley (Newgrange, Knowth, Dowth) and the many historic sights of Ireland's ancient east (Hill of Tara, Slane Castle, Trim castle etc)
The cottage itself is part of a farm house with working yard/small farm with dogs/cats and horses/donkeys and livestock in the adjoining fields so plenty of country walks to see the beautiful Meath countryside if you don't fancy getting back in the car!
you can find out more online @trohannycottage/trohannycottage.ie

name: Apartment in Dublin city centre
description:
Modern top floor apartment in a fantastic location. Walking distance from the city centre and 5 minutes from the famous Trinity College. Great accessibility for Dart (train) and Luas (tram) lines. Close to Grand Canal and also the river Liffey.

The space
Wonderful location in the heart of Dublin. Adjacent to the River Liffey and the Samuel Beckett bridge there are plenty of great places to go for walks day and night with some great views of Dublin.

Guest access
Your bedroom, the bathroom, living room, kitchen and balcony
neighborhoodOverview: Lovely setting as the apartment looks onto a small green with tree covered pathways leading in. Very secure location with 2 security doors to pass through before reaching our apartment door.

name: Castletownmoor Clinic & Permaculture Farm - single
description:
We promote a back to nature way of life & respect for the environment.

Wifi is available but purposely not in bedrooms as we aim to have low EMF exposure for ourselves & guests.

The space
We promote a back to nature way of life & respect for the environment.
Being mindful of water consumption is appreciated, as we run from a small natural well.

Warm stove is lit and there is a range of books and travel guides to explore.
Wifi is available in communal rooms.
Tea and coffee making facilities in-room upon request - please just ask. Key lock on all bedroom doors.

There is plenty of space to find yourself outdoors among the herbs, plants and trees that hold our space - an ideal retreat accommodation.

Holistic therapies available at additional charge including herbal medicine, massage, refexology, nutrition and dietetics.

Regular fire ceremonies, training and workshops - see castletownmoor clinic
neighborhoodOverview:
Rural Ireland, located 1 mile from boglands, forestry and in the other direction a grocery store.
By car: 30minute drive to Newgrange, Hill of Tara, Bective Abbey, 40mins to Drogheda and Trim, 12minute drive to Kells Heritage town. 1 hour by car to Dublin and the airport.

name: Cozy room on the heart of the city!
description:
We are a couple who got a place in the city center of Dublin. The apartment is recently reformed Duplex design, which gives independency between common areas and rooms.

Near to LUAS rail (-5min) and Train DART station (15min), also to main Bus lines.

It is very close of the main streets and neighbourhoods like O'Connell Street (5min) or Temple Bar (5-10min). Less than 3 minutes walking to supermarkets like Aldi, Tesco or Lidl, and just below our building there is 24 hours Centra minimarket.

The space
Our apartment is a newly reformed Duplex. In the top floor is where the rooms and the bathroom is located, which is independent and isolated from the common areas like the living room or the kitchen.

We are currently living as owners in the apartment. It is fully equipped with everything you will need, clean and cosy.

There is a cat living in the house, which likes people but is very independent, so you will not notice it
neighborhoodOverview: The Neighbourhood is close to main interesting points, but also so quiet as our place faces the inside of our building, so you will hear no car and sounds from the outside, this actually helps to sleep as Dublin can be noisy.

name: 3 min walk from Temple Bar! City centre location!
description:
The apartment consists of 2 bedrooms, living room, kitchen & a bathroom. All windows are facing the courtyard so even though you are right in the middle of city centre, the place is very quiet.

-3 min walk to Temple Bar
-2 min walk to Henry street
-10 min walk to Grafton street

-15 min walk to St Patrick Cathedral
-10 min walk to Christchurch Cathedral
-5 min by taxi to Guinness Storhse

The space

All main Dublin attractions are within walking distance, and those who need to go anywhere outside of the city centre, you will find Luas stop only a min walk from my place.

Dublin maps are provided and I am happy to talk you

Guest access

Other th
neighborhoodOverview:
The house is in the Liberties which is one of Dublin’s oldest and most fascinating areas which is a short walking distance to many historical attractions such as Christchurch Cathedral, Teelings Whiskey Distillery, Jameson Distillery, Guinness Storehouse, St. Patricks Cathedral and Kilmainham Gaol.

There are also many café’s, restaurants and bars around the area as well as the house being located just off Francis Street which is known as Dublin’s main Antique street. Meath Street is at the other end of my street which is home to the famous Liberty Market (Thursday-Saturday) and many shops and eateries.

There is also a flea market which takes place in Newmarket Square on the last Sunday of every month and this would take approximately 5 minutes to reach by foot.

This area is very popular with tourists considering its history and how centrally located it is, it really is a perfect location if you are looking to visit and experience all of what this great

name: Contemporary Apartment  Dublin City
description:
A stunning 2 bed / 2 bath apartment on the river in Dublin City Center. Comfortable & modern, south facing with roof deck and a 5 minute walk to Temple Bar and all tourist attractions. Everything you need for the perfect stay in this charming city.

The space
Big open loft style. The Apt is south facing on the Quays and the bedrooms are totally quiet as they face away from the Quays. Idyllic and peaceful with all modern conveniences. This is a very chilled and comfortable apartment with a big comfy sofa that will sleep a 5th person.

Dublin's famous Smithfield square is literally across the river facing the apartment. There are a number of very trendy, good value restaurants with amazing food 2 minutes away on Benburb St. The art house cinema "The Light House" is across the street also on the square

name: Quaint Townhouse by Phoenix Park, near city centre
description:
This is a lovely quaint Victorian house located in an historic part of old Dublin. The Phoenix park, Guinness Storehouse, The National Museum & Heuston station, among other attractions, are all within walking distance, as are the Luas and all main bus routes. O' Connell Street is 15 minutes by Luas. The neighbourhood is friendly and safe

I am in the process of modernising my new home but it looks nice, feels comfortable and cosy and I have everything I need in the heart of this vibrant city!

The space
My house is a two bed terraced house in Dublin 7, in a safe and friendly housing estate. The downstairs is open plan and the kitchen has been newly renovated. The living space is a nice size for you to sit back and relax, watch T.V or read. There is a dining table beside the front window where you can work or dine. I like to have my morning coffee here and watch the city pass! The bathroom is downstairs too and has a toilet and electric shower. The
neighborhoodOverview: Dublin 7 is a great part of Dublin and I really enjoy living here.  I regularly go running and walking in the Phoenix Park which is within a stones throw from my front door.  Stoneybatter, the lovely neighbourhood behind my housing estate has a number of new cafés with excellent barista coffee, for those who enjoy it! Some of my favourites are Slice, Love Supreme or Proper Order Coffee in Smithfield.  Likewise there are numerous modern eateries in the area, all the way in towards O' Connell street.  Tourist attractions abound: The Phoenix Park, The Guinness Storehouse, IMMA, The Royal Hospital and Kilmainham Gaol are all nearby within walking distance.  Otherwise the RHA, The National Gallery of Ireland, Hugh Lane Gallery are other excellent galleries for art lovers.  Shopping is endless, as are options for music, theatre and restaurants!

description:
Exceptionally comfortable two bedroom apartment ideally located in the heart of Dublin 7 (Smithfield). The property is within minutes walking distance of many of Dublin's main attractions, including Guinness & Jameson Storehouse's.

This modernly decorated living space is both comfortable and spacious, and includes all the necessary amenities to ensure a very comfortable stay (SKY Satellite TV included).

Suitable for business and long term bookings, but of course we cater for all bookings.

The space

neighborhoodOverview:
Smithfield is an incredibly thriving area, and contains some of Dublin's coolest bars and restaurants. Please see Trip Advisor for more info on same.

The apartment is located above Smithfield square which hosts regular arts, crafts and music events.

One of Dublins top Gym's is located in the same block. The gym boats state of the art equipment, pool, sauna, spa etc.
See "Oneescape gym" for more details.

The Lighthouse cinema is also located within same apartment complex. This cinema is extremely popular for the less mainstream movie goers, and always offers a very classy show list.

Quick fire local recommendations:

Best all round bar – Oscars – Great food and beers.
Best Guinness – Walsh's, Manor st.
Best craft beer – Mulligans, manor street – Great food too.

Frank Rya

name: Funky town house in Old City
description:
Bright, warm house, originally built in the 1920s in a wonderful, historic part of Dublin. A great base from which to explore the city by foot, and a cosy space to relax after a long day (or night!).

The space
I live in a lovely part of the city, full of artists and close to great cafes - it's a quiet neighbourhood that's just a short walk from the hustle and bustle of the city centre. The house warm and cosy with open fires, and gets loads of natural light.
The upstairs bedrooms are quiet and calm spaces, each with an old fireplace, and really comfortable double beds with a quality mattress. The bathroom is adjacent the bedrooms. There's a third small bedroom downstairs off the kitchen.
There's a full kitchen, dining & living area and rear patio which you are free to use as you please, as well as a separate cosy sitting room if you want to chill out and read a book by the fire.

There is great free wi-fi, but note that there's no TV.
neighborhoodOverview:
Dublin, Ireland
I really love Dublin 8 - it's the perfect mix of all the weird and wonderful things the city has to offer. It's chilled, it's lively, it's often gritty and it's home to tons of art, design and music studios.
It's a lovely piece of old Dublin, the neighbourhood having been constructed in 1923 on a field that was once used for drying and hanging the textiles of the cotton industry, hence the name, The Tenters. In some ways it feels like it's far away from the city, it's so calm. There's a great mix of people living in the area, from artists and actors to the typical Dublin 'aul wans', and plenty of funky cafes and proper old Dublin pubs just a short walk away. Though it's not quite in the centre of the action, everything you could need is a few minutes away.

If you're visiting Dublin, you'll probably want to see the Guinness storehouse which is just 5 minutes by foot - you can smell the hops and malted barley on a good day- and there's plenty of grea

The space

Guest access

neighborhoodOverview:
Just North of the River Liffey and a short walk from historic O'Connell Street, this is the very heart of the city centre and the perfect location for anyone wishing to explore the city by foot.

One of Dublin’s main shopping hubs is O'Connell Street (and its tributary, the ever-busy Henry Street), which culminates in a spearhead of excellent museums dotted around Parnell Square (most notably the Hugh Lane Gallery). To the west of here is the up-and-coming Smithfield and, further still, the vast Phoenix Park (also home to Dublin Zoo) while just across the bridge to the south is the formidable campus of Trinity College, with its ancient claim to fame in pride of place in the Old Library & Book of Kells.

You have everything at your doorstep in the city centre and there's an exciting mix of cultures and ideas to cater for every whim you might have.

Please take a look at the guidebook on my listing for recommended places to eat and drink in the area!

The space

It’s a simple, calm space with a separate bedroom, living area and a compact kitchen, allowing you to enjoy a home-cooked meal and relax when you need to take a break from city touring, or if you just want to whip something together after a day's work!

The bedroom offers a double bed and plenty of storage space. The living area also has a pull-out sofa that is easy to use and comfortable. So this is a great option not just for solo travellers and couples, but also
neighborhoodOverview:
This is the perfect location if you like to explore different neighbourhoods that the city has to offer. Situated in the Liberties, which is one of Dublin’s most historic neighbourhoods, you will exit the apartment complex and come face to face with a large section of wall that once formed one of Dublin’s medieval boundaries. Around the corner is Christchurch Cathedral, a magnificent structure and one of Dublin’s top tourist attractions. Dublin Castle and St Patrick's Cathedral are also 5 minutes from the apartment. Walk a few meters and also you arrive at the Guinness Storehouse, an important landmark that holds great significance for Irish and visitors alike!

Once you’ve had your fill of historic wonders, you may wish to take a walk up Francis Street, the start of which is just to the rear of the property. Francis street is full to the brim of antique shops and bric a brac, for anyone who likes to discover old Irish hidden gems. At the other end of Francis Street you will

description:

Guest access

neighborhoodOverview: The Liberties is a traditional working class Dublin neighbourhood that is currently going through a process of gentrification with the opening of trendy cafes and pubs, hotels and student residences in the area. neighborhoodOverview:
Dublin 8 has become very popular with artists and creatives. Some great cafes and restaurants near by. Fumbally cafe and market just 3 minutes walk! Teelings distillery just 2 minutes walk!
Finest asset of the city St. Stephens Green is just 10 minutes walk and you pass St. Patrick's Cathedral on the way. Camden street is full of bars and restaurants and is just 10 minutes walk. You won't have to spend any money on taxis!
Our local bar Fallon's (on the street) is one on the finest in Dublin. Somewhere to have a quiet Guiness on a sunny afternoon or stay local on a Friday night when it fills up.

name: Pine Shepherd's Hut (2-man wagon)
description:
Pine is one of our sweet Shepherd Huts. It has been traditionally designed and has a beautifully crafted interior. Boasting a kingsize bed it creates a cosy and romantic space perfect for two people or couple sharing.

The space
This is a beautifully crafted Shepherd's Hut (wagon on wheels used by shepherds and railway signalmen in times gone by). Pine has its own small but highly efficient stove with a continual supply of eco-firelighters, kindling and firewood to keep you super cosy. We will help you light your fires and keep you warm with plenty of wood during your stay.
Pine is located on our secluded woodland hideaway Glamping area with its own communal facilities (kitchen, showers, toilets and seating areas). In Winter Pine is moved to a more sheltered location by the main Glamping facilities and shares the whole Glamping field overlooking Slane Castle with just one other shepherd's hut Apple. This Glamping area also has a BBQ, wood-fired hot tub and cl
neighborhoodOverview: Slane is one of the best known heritage villages in Ireland. Thanks to the rock concerts at Slane Castle and now the new whiskey distillery, Slane now has a vibrant food and music culture with restaurants, cafes and bistros as well as great live music pubs. Be sure to book in on a Wednesday night to see the Wednesday Gang open session in Boyle's of Slane and don't forget to book a tour around the new Slane Distillery. We are also only 6km from the UNESCO World Heritage megalithics tombs at Bru Na Boinne (Newgrange) and only 8km from the Battle of the Boyne centre. We also offer kayaking, recreational tree climbing and bike hire to keep you busy while you're here.

neighborhoodOverview:
Rialto is in the south city area of Dublin, on the South Circular Road, 30 minute walk from the city centre. This is a very old part of the city. Many houses in Rialto were build for the Guinness workers, the brewery is nearby.

A few minutes away is the Grand Canal which circles the city on the south side. It is a lovely walk or cycle to follow the canal all the way to the grand canal basin.

A short cycle to the north of Rialto is Phoenix Park, the largest walled city park in Europe. Very close by is Kilmainham Gaol (you may need to book a tour ahead of time), The Irish Museum Of Modern Art and The War Memorial Park at Islandbridge. Three stops on the tram will take you to The National Museum at Collins Barracks.

Herberton Leisure is a gym that is a few minutes walk away. They have daily or weekly rates available. Hertz Rental Car on the South Circular Road is a 20 minute walk.

5 mins walk to Christchurch Cathedral, 10 mins to Temple Bar, 15 mins to Stephen's Green.

The apartment is not modern, but it is comfortable. If you are looking to save on accommodation on a busy weekend in Dublin, this is a good central option in the area known as The Liberties, one of the oldest parts of Dublin city.

Please tell me as early as possible, preferably upon making the booking, what time you will arrive so that I can plan to be there

Guest access
You have access to the entire apartment (except my bedroom!)
neighborhoodOverview:
The area is known as The Liberties. It was the very first area of Dublin city to be built up outside of the original city walls, almost 1000 years ago. As such, the laws of the city did not apply, and residents were "at liberty" to do as they pleased!!
Unfortunately, the laws apply to everyone in the area nowadays, but The Liberties has a lovely mix of "old Dublin" and an element of gentrification which brings nice restaurants, pubs and coffee shops to an area just 15 minutes walk to Trinity College.

name: Gold Ensuite Room - The Harp by Nestor Life - City View
description:
Hello and thanks for taking a look at The Harp by Nestor Life!

We’ve converted Dublin’s best student building into a popup co-living space for the summer - offering great value, modern ensuite rooms right next to the Guinness storeroom!

We have a fun, social vibe and we’ll gladly tell you about all of the best events taking place around Dublin. You’ll also have use of our modern gym and common room with pool table, Smart TV and more.

We look forward to meeting you! :)

The space
The rooms have contemporary decor and an ensuite bathroom and you’ll have access to a shared kitchen with all the amenities you need.

What To Expect:
* A comfortable room with contemporary furnishings and laptop friendly desk space
* 3/4 size double beds. 120cm x 190cm. 3ft 11inch x 6ft 2inch
* Ensuite bathroom
* All linen and 2 towels provided
* Access to an on-site modern gym, common room and pool table
* Acces
neighborhoodOverview:
Dublin is a compact and walkable city with a reputation for being fun-loving and friendly, and with good reason!

You’ll love discovering the sociable pub culture and traditional music scene of this historic city - and with more than 1000 pubs in the capital, you’ll be spoilt for choice. If you fancy sampling some proper Irish whiskey, Jameson Distillery has been in Dublin for more than 200 years and offers great tasting sessions.

Temple Bar is famous for being a hub of nightlife, but it’s also Dublin’s cultural heart, with the Irish Photography Centre, Irish Film Institute and the Temple Bar Book Market all in this vibrant neighbourhood.

Dublin’s Creative Quarter is also a short walk away - home to artisan boutiques, art studios, cafés, galleries and plenty of great restaurants. Not to mention all the historically important sites like St Patrick’s Cathedral, Trinity College and Dublin Castle that the city has to offer.

And of course, no tr

description:
This spacious Spacious Loft Apartment is nestled comfortably within the trendy Kilmainham area, just outside of the busy city centre, and among some of the most popular tourist draws in the capital. The D8 area offers a comfortable and centralized approach to exploring Dublin for your tourist or business purposes.

The space
The general living space boasts natural light and cleanliness. There is a full kitchen equipped with cooking facilities and all utensils. Additionally, there is a comfortable living room with a large TV and comfortable sofa for your use. The room itself is very welcoming with it’s spacious and clean aesthetic. This shared apartment let’s one comfortable double bedroom; with private ensuite, plenty of extra pillows, dresser and closet & full length mirror. Some complimentary toiletries are provided as well as other room amenities such as towels. If necessary, a vacuum and other cleaning supplies are available for use.

Guest acces
neighborhoodOverview: The surrounding area is extremely accessible to the city centre by train, tram/luas, and bus. Alternatively, if you enjoy a stroll, a 30 minute scenic walk will take you directly into the city centre/Temple Bar area. If you choose to bring a vehicle, there is street parking also available for a fee (parking can be limited, and sometimes challenging). There are numerous pubs, eateries, a grocery store, and pharmacy just steps away from the door for your convenience - I’d be happy to make recommendations upon request. Nearby attractions include the Irish Museum of Modern Art, located directly across the street from the apartment, with the Kilmainham Gaol then directly behind the museum. Situated within the “Digital Hub”, other nearby attractions include the National Museum of Ireland, Dublin Zoo/Phoenix Park, St. James Hospital, and the famous Guinness Brewery, all within walking distance of the apartment.

The balcony looks over the lovely river Liffey and onto the Guinness factory!

The space

If you are a family staying we have all the accessories one might need to entertain. If not we will have them put away and out of sight.

With three double sized bedrooms and two bathrooms, this home makes a very suitable short term living option. It is all set up with all you would require to just slot in as a home from home.

The space
The main living space has an open kitchen with a family sitting and dining area. The kitchen is well equipped with all you need including an oven, hob, dishwasher, toaster, kettle, etc. It has an island suitable for casual dining or extra workspace.

There is a dining table that opens out if required for extra diners and a family area with corner sofa facing a tv. This area also faces a raised double sided fireplace whi

Boating, walking, fishing, horse-riding, golfing, cycling and culture are all on offer in a nearby radius.

description:

A superb full Irish breakfast* with home baked breads, is included with accommodation.

A delicious, home cooked dinner in the evening, using only superb, locally sourced food, is also available.
Check photos to see some of our dishes. Ask for sample dinner menus and prices.
*vegetarian/ vegan options

The space
We live in a pretty country house that dates back to 1869. It's a warm, cosy home, full of character and charm, with lovely views of the Westmeath countryside.

Our home is bright and comfortable but it IS a 150 year-old house so, please note that it's shabby chic and cosy, rather than immaculately perfect!
And we are strictly a no smoking household.

We are right in the heart of Ireland, Ireland's lake district, rich in Gaelic legends,
neighborhoodOverview:

Newly opened Centreparcs is a 5 minute drive. We are 20-25 minutes from local towns, Mullingar, Athlone and Longford.
Dublin and Galway are both a 75-90 minute drive away.

The area is well-connected by bus and light rail to the city centre, and there are several rental bike stations close by.

The living room/kitchen overlooks the green areas in the back. It is bright and quiet.

Guest access

Our double room, is en-suite and can sleep 3, is light bright, south facing, over looking our rear garden and countryside. description:
Bright, modern apartment located in the historic quarter of Dublin. Just 10 minutes walk from Grafton Street and Stephens Green.

The apartment has been recently refurbished with all new furniture.

Perfect for couples or families who wish to visit Dublin and be able to walk everywhere.

The space
I bought my apartment recently and have spent time refurbishing it and getting it just right. I'd added my own personal style that I think you'll enjoy.

Located in a secure block, the apartment delivers the benefits of being within walking distance of the city without the hustle and bustle of being right in the middle.

Guest access
Guests will have access to the entire property.

Located in the historic Liberties area of Dublin, you are close to lots of cool cafes and restaurants.
The famous Two Pups Coffee shop and cafe is just 60 seconds walk from the apartment. Highly recommend starting your day here!

Bright and cosy one bedroom apartment, sleeps 2 people in the heart of the Liberties in Dublin, walking distance to the city center and 5 minutes walk to the Guinness Store House, the newly opened Teelings distillery and St. Patrick Cathedral.

The space
One bedroom apartment with a double bed. The sofa in the living room pulls out into a small double bed. As a result this apartment can sleep two in separate beds or a couple and a child.

Guest access
Guests will have access to the whole apartment except the wardrobes in the bedroom but space for guest clothes will be provided.
neighborhoodOverview: Located in the Liberties in Dublin 8, experience both old and new Dublin. Dublin 8 is rapidly becoming known as one of 'the' trendy areas in Dublin but it is also shrouded in history and character. Start the day off with breakfast in the very trendy Fumbally cafe, take a stroll through St. Patrick's park or visit the Cathedral. Spend the afternoon investigating the hidden treasures in the antique shops on Francis St. whiskey tasting in Teelings Distillery,  or taking in the views of the city from the top of the Guinness storehouse and then finish the day in the local Fallons pub and meet some of the locals.

name: City Centre Location -Double bed

Clean, bright apartment located within walking distance of all Dublin's major tourist attractions. The room has a double bed and fresh sheets for you to relax in after enjoying Dublin's entertainment. The room is very clean and bright with plenty of storage. Towels and toiletries are provided.
There is a separate bathroom with an electric shower.

The space
The apartment is very clean and tidy and there is a fully equipped kitchen if you want to dine in. We have high speed broadband and TV with Netflix if you decide to sit in with a glass of wine after a long day on the tourist trail.
But mainly it's all about the location. Temple bar, Grafton Street, Guinness storehouse, the Book of Kells etc are all within ten minutes walk.

Guest access
You will have full access to the kitchen and living room. The bathroom is shared.
neighborhoodOverview:
This is a great location to explore all Dublin has to offer. It is in the city centre so you can walk everywhere in minutes but you don't get the hassle and constant noise of the Temple Bar area. St Patrick's cathedral is outside the front door and Christchurch is four minutes walk. Temple bar is about 8 minutes and the shops of Grafton Street are about ten.
If walking isn't your thing there is a bus stop outside the door with routes that take you into O'Connell Street, the IFSC and the Docklands.

name: Comfortable Modern 1-bed Apartment
description:
Comfortable one bedroom apartment with contemporary decor. Perfect for 2-4 guests, with a pull out corner sofa bed in the lounge.

**Currently being refurbished, new photos will be added in the next few days.**

On lovely grounds, close to the Guinness factory and the beautiful Irish War Memorial Gardens, on the banks of the river Liffey. Frequent bus route to the city centre right outside (10 min journey).

The space
The apartment complex is situated in spacious, leafy, quiet grounds, well off the road.

Guest access
Access to the entire apartment - Living room with fully equipped kitchen, bedroom, bathroom and balcony.

Other things to note
The apartment is located on the third floor. There is an elevator. Although located next to a railway, the apartment is otherwise very quiet.
neighborhoodOverview: Seven Oaks Apartments is a complex of seven blocks built on lovely green grounds, surrounding a former convent. The estate holds many rewards for the best maintained property within the neighbourhood. The apartment is overlooking our allotment - the pride of the residents of Seven Oaks (access available on request).

name: Dublin City Centre, Single Room
description:
Perfect for the solo traveller on a short visit to Dublin. Very comfortable single room in a charming house very close to the city centre. Many tourist attractions in walking distance, as well as the famous Temple Bar area! €35 Sun-Thur, €40 Fri/Sat

The space
The listing is my spare room which is a single room with bed, locker and space to hang clothes. Guests are provided with a bath towel and a hand towel. Light breakfast is included in rate.

This is my home so I will likely be here during your stay. Happy to help with any queries on the locality and getting around, recommendations etc, but equally respect your privacy and want you to feel comfortable in your surroundings.

The neighbourhood is very conveniently located between Christchurch Cathedral and St Patrick's Cathedral. A short stroll to Temple Bar, Grafton Street, St Stephen's Green. Ample choice of bars and restaurants in close proximity!

In walking distance of all cen

name: Toms Cottage In The Lake County
description:
Welcome to Toms Cottage. Nestled securely behind our family home it’s a cosy & welcoming space to enjoy with friends or family. We re situated in the beautiful lake county & being 1hr from Dublin and Galway we are uniquely positioned to explore the island. 20 mins drive to Mullingar & 15 mins drive to Tullamore towns. Belvedere house & gardens 20 min drive. Lilliput/Johnathon Swift park 10 mins Druid Glamping - 5 mins away.

The space
The cottage comprises of two bedrooms with a double bed in each. Beautifully decorated and very welcoming. It has a living area with kitchen and seating. You will even find NETFLIX on the flat screen smart tv. One of the couches is a sofa bed. The cottage has 1 shared bathroom with a large walk in shower.

Guest access
You will have the entire cottage to yourself and whoever you are traveling with. Our outside space is a large shared area of gardens. Securely fenced and surround by a beautiful beech hedge
<
neighborhoodOverview: The cottage is in a country location and only a 5 minute drive to Castletown village with its local pubs and Mount Druid Glamping and wedding destination. 1 km from the scenic little village of Ballinagore. If you enjoy walking or hiking the beautiful Westmeath way is on our door step. And for interested golfers we are convenient to 4 championship golf courses - Mullingar, Tullamore, New forest and Shane Lowry ‘s Esker hills.

name: Beautiful double room
description:
Double room with strong wifi in a beautiful 2 bed apartment in Kilmainham. Available again from mid August following renovations. Close to Guinness storehouse, Airport shuttle and walking distance to city centre and Phoenix Park with lots of public transport options. Midweek check-in before 10 am or after 4 pm but may be available to facilitate other times ( depending on work schedule!) but check in any time at weekends.

The space
Situated in quiet complex with mature grounds. The Dublin Bus Hop on Hop off sightseeing tour stops right outside and the apartment is a few minutes walk to the Guinness Storehouse. Perfect base from which to explore the city!

Guest access
Guests will have access to wifi, tv, fridge, washing machine, dishwasher, microwave, towels, quality bed linen, shampoo, conditioner, tooth paste etc. and anything you might have forgotten to bring! Selection of Cereals, bread, juice and fruit provided for breakfast but it is un
neighborhoodOverview: Beautiful complex with mature trees and river running through it. It is quiet yet very accessible to city centre.

name: Modern home by Guinness Storehouse
description:
Our modern fifth floor apartment is located just five minutes from Ireland's top tourist attraction, the Guinness Storehouse. This is a spacious place with two double bedrooms, two bathrooms, ample living and kitchen area, and two balconies, one overlooking the Phoenix Park and another on a private courtyard. You'll be in the city centre in 15 minutes on the tram, which stops directly outside our building. Or, grab a Dublin Bike and cycle along the canal to the south side.

The space
Bedrooms: one double room with a superking size bed and ensuite with shower. Second bedroom has a double bed and a bathroom with a bath and shower next door. Both rooms look out onto a balcony with views of Kilmainham and the Phoenix Park. The living space is big and bright, with a large dining table and a kitchen with everything you'll need to eat in. Our smaller south-facing balcony is home to our little garden, and you should feel free to help yourself to mint, thyme, rosemary and
neighborhoodOverview: Our neighbourhood is so convenient for the city centre, Phoenix Park, the Irish Museum of Modern Art, the Guinness Storehouse and the Teeling Whiskey Distillery. We love how easy it is to hop on the tram, which leaves very regularly from right outside the building. It's a family neighbourhood with a traditional Dublin feel - you're likely to hear horses and carts trotting by from the nearby stables! There are supermarkets just a short walk away too.
